{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780925357710,"sessionID":"ses_158954ac7ffeX00Y2fH37dXkNJ","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_fbh8JvSn1AIpSRGpdbriXZxx","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/ARCHITECTURE.md","offset":100,"limit":60},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/ARCHITECTURE.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n100: \n101: - `scripts/ ──▶ mcp_server/api/`\n102: - `mcp_server/ ──▶ shared/`\n103: - `scripts/ ──▶ shared/`\n104: - `mcp_server/ ──▶ database/`\n105: \n106: Reverse imports are blocked by lint and CI.\n107: \n108: ---\n109: \n110: ## 3. CANONICAL CONTINUITY FLOWS\n111: \n112: Spec-kit treats canonical spec documents as the durable continuity record. Generated memory indexes are search/recall surfaces over that record, not the record itself.\n113: \n114: **Read path (`/spec_kit:resume`):**\n115: \n116: 1. Look for `handover.md` at the spec folder root.\n117: 2. Fall back to `_memory.continuity` frontmatter blocks inside `implementation-summary.md`.\n118: 3. Fall back to canonical spec docs in this order: `implementation-summary.md`, `tasks.md`, `plan.md`, `spec.md`.\n119: 4. Surface graph-metadata pointers (`derived.last_active_child_id`, `derived.last_active_at`) for phase parents.\n120: \n121: **Write path (`/memory:save`):**\n122: \n123: 1. AI composes structured JSON describing session context.\n124: 2. `generate-context.js` routes content into the right canonical doc (`implementation-summary.md`, `decision-record.md`, `handover.md`) and refreshes `description.json` + `graph-metadata.json`.\n125: 3. The indexed-continuity store re-indexes the touched docs for hybrid retrieval.\n126: \n127: **Key modules:**\n128: \n129: - `mcp_server/lib/resume/` owns the read path.\n130: - `scripts/dist/memory/generate-context.js` owns the write path.\n131: - `mcp_server/lib/continuity/` owns the indexing layer.\n132: \n133: ---\n134: \n135: ## 4. RUNTIME SUBSYSTEMS\n136: \n137: The MCP server is composed of focused subsystems that share the transport layer and the SQLite store.\n138: \n139: **Search.** The 5-channel hybrid retrieval pipeline (Vector, FTS5, BM25, Causal Graph, Degree) lives in `lib/search/`. The four pipeline stages are Gather → Score → Rerank → Filter. Reciprocal Rank Fusion combines channel outputs. Response shaping happens in `formatters/`.\n140: \n141: **Memory and continuity.** `lib/memory/` owns the indexed-continuity store schema and persistence. `lib/continuity/` owns the canonical-doc routing. `database/` carries the SQLite files (`memory.db`, `embeddings.db`, plus auxiliary stores).\n142: \n143: **Save pipeline.** `handlers/save/` runs the 3-layer save gate (intake validation, content router, post-save quality review). DQI scoring runs on every save.\n144: \n145: **Hook orchestrator.** `hooks/{claude,gemini,copilot,codex}/` produce per-runtime startup, prompt-submit, and compact-context payloads. The payloads share a common builder in `lib/hooks/`.\n146: \n147: **Matrix runners.** `matrix_runners/` houses the F1-F14 evaluation harness and per-CLI adapters used by the quality matrix.\n148: \n149: **Stress tests.** `stress_test/` carries opt-in load + degraded-state suites, excluded from default `npm test` and run through `npm run stress`.\n150: \n151: ---\n152: \n153: ## 5. HOOK AND PLUGIN INTEGRATION\n154: \n155: Spec-kit ships a runtime hook surface that wires into each AI client's session lifecycle. The hooks emit compact context payloads at `SessionStart`, `UserPromptSubmit`, and (where supported) `Compact`.\n156: \n157: **Hook matrix.** Claude Code and Gemini CLI inject prompt-time briefs directly. Codex CLI supports native `SessionStart` and `UserPromptSubmit` hooks when `[features].codex_hooks = true` in `~/.codex/config.toml` and `~/.codex/hooks.json` is wired. OpenCode delivers context through a plugin bridge under `.opencode/plugins/`. Copilot CLI refreshes a managed block in `$HOME/.copilot/copilot-instructions.md` because Copilot hook stdout is not prompt-mutating.\n158: \n159: **Plugin bridges.** OpenCode plugin entrypoints live under `.opencode/plugins/`. Each plugin imports a thin bridge that calls into `mcp_server/lib/hooks/` and emits a payload back to the runtime.\n\n(Showing lines 100-159 of 199. Use offset=160 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"\n- `scripts/ ──▶ mcp_server/api/`\n- `mcp_server/ ──▶ shared/`\n- `scripts/ ──▶ shared/`\n- `mcp_server/ ──▶ database/`\n\nReverse imports are blocked by lint and CI.\n\n---\n\n## 3. CANONICAL CONTINUITY FLOWS\n\nSpec-kit treats canonical spec documents as the durable continuity record. Generated memory indexes are search/recall surfaces over that record, not the record itself.\n\n**Read path (`/spec_kit:resume`):**\n\n1. Look for `handover.md` at the spec folder root.\n2. Fall back to `_memory.continuity` frontmatter blocks inside `implementation-summary.md`.\n3. Fall back to canonical spec docs in this order: `implementation-summary.md`, `tasks.md`, `plan.md`, `spec.md`.\n4. Surface graph-metadata pointers (`derived.last_active_child_id`, `derived.last_active_at`) for phase parents.","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/ARCHITECTURE.md","text":"\n- `scripts/ ──▶ mcp_server/api/`\n- `mcp_server/ ──▶ shared/`\n- `scripts/ ──▶ shared/`\n- `mcp_server/ ──▶ database/`\n\nReverse imports are blocked by lint and CI.\n\n---\n\n## 3. CANONICAL CONTINUITY FLOWS\n\nSpec-kit treats canonical spec documents as the durable continuity record. Generated memory indexes are search/recall surfaces over that record, not the record itself.\n\n**Read path (`/spec_kit:resume`):**\n\n1. Look for `handover.md` at the spec folder root.\n2. Fall back to `_memory.continuity` frontmatter blocks inside `implementation-summary.md`.\n3. Fall back to canonical spec docs in this order: `implementation-summary.md`, `tasks.md`, `plan.md`, `spec.md`.\n4. Surface graph-metadata pointers (`derived.last_active_child_id`, `derived.last_active_at`) for phase parents.\n\n**Write path (`/memory:save`):**\n\n1. AI composes structured JSON describing session context.\n2. `generate-context.js` routes content into the right canonical doc (`implementation-summary.md`, `decision-record.md`, `handover.md`) and refreshes `description.json` + `graph-metadata.json`.\n3. The indexed-continuity store re-indexes the touched docs for hybrid retrieval.\n\n**Key modules:**\n\n- `mcp_server/lib/resume/` owns the read path.\n- `scripts/dist/memory/generate-context.js` owns the write path.\n- `mcp_server/lib/continuity/` owns the indexing layer.\n\n---\n\n## 4. RUNTIME SUBSYSTEMS\n\nThe MCP server is composed of focused subsystems that share the transport layer and the SQLite store.\n\n**Search.** The 5-channel hybrid retrieval pipeline (Vector, FTS5, BM25, Causal Graph, Degree) lives in `lib/search/`. The four pipeline stages are Gather → Score → Rerank → Filter. Reciprocal Rank Fusion combines channel outputs. Response shaping happens in `formatters/`.\n\n**Memory and continuity.** `lib/memory/` owns the indexed-continuity store schema and persistence. `lib/continuity/` owns the canonical-doc routing. `database/` carries the SQLite files (`memory.db`, `embeddings.db`, plus auxiliary stores).\n\n**Save pipeline.** `handlers/save/` runs the 3-layer save gate (intake validation, content router, post-save quality review). DQI scoring runs on every save.\n\n**Hook orchestrator.** `hooks/{claude,gemini,copilot,codex}/` produce per-runtime startup, prompt-submit, and compact-context payloads. The payloads share a common builder in `lib/hooks/`.\n\n**Matrix runners.** `matrix_runners/` houses the F1-F14 evaluation harness and per-CLI adapters used by the quality matrix.\n\n**Stress tests.** `stress_test/` carries opt-in load + degraded-state suites, excluded from default `npm test` and run through `npm run stress`.\n\n---\n\n## 5. HOOK AND PLUGIN INTEGRATION\n\nSpec-kit ships a runtime hook surface that wires into each AI client's session lifecycle. The hooks emit compact context payloads at `SessionStart`, `UserPromptSubmit`, and (where supported) `Compact`.\n\n**Hook matrix.** Claude Code and Gemini CLI inject prompt-time briefs directly. Codex CLI supports native `SessionStart` and `UserPromptSubmit` hooks when `[features].codex_hooks = true` in `~/.codex/config.toml` and `~/.codex/hooks.json` is wired. OpenCode delivers context through a plugin bridge under `.opencode/plugins/`. Copilot CLI refreshes a managed block in `$HOME/.copilot/copilot-instructions.md` because Copilot hook stdout is not prompt-mutating.\n\n**Plugin bridges.** OpenCode plugin entrypoints live under `.opencode/plugins/`. Each plugin imports a thin bridge that calls into `mcp_server/lib/hooks/` and emits a payload back to the runtime.","lineStart":100,"lineEnd":159,"totalLines":199,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/ARCHITECTURE.md","time":{"start":1780925357692,"end":1780925357699}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0f5bcb161580130a016a26c3ad9cfc81919c323289e3067331"}},"id":"prt_ea76c5e550014OCMpSKdCWpaXb","sessionID":"ses_158954ac7ffeX00Y2fH37dXkNJ","messageID":"msg_ea76c3e63001uhwXOldtDAOrVn"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780925357724,"sessionID":"ses_158954ac7ffeX00Y2fH37dXkNJ","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_UFpmN6kf9NFC9D2DGd28xxAO","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/README.md","offset":90,"limit":110},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/README.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n90: \n91: Start a new session on work you did before:\n92: \n93: ```text\n94: /speckit:resume\n95: ```\n96: \n97: The system rebuilds continuation context in a fixed order: `handover.md` first, then `_memory.continuity`, then the packet's canonical spec docs. It presents the current state, prior decisions, touched files and next steps before you start.\n98: \n99: ### Search for Context\n100: \n101: Ask the indexed-continuity store a question in plain language:\n102: \n103: ```text\n104: /memory:search \"how did we decide on the auth architecture?\"\n105: ```\n106: \n107: The system reads your question, figures out you are looking for a past decision and routes to the right search strategy automatically.\n108: \n109: ### Validate a Spec Folder\n110: \n111: ```bash\n112: # Run all 20 validation rules\n113: bash .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/spec/validate.sh \\\n114:   .opencode/specs/[project]/042-my-feature/\n115: \n116: # Exit 0 = success, Exit 1 = user error, Exit 2 = validation error, Exit 3 = system error\n117: ```\n118: \n119: ### Verify the MCP Is Running\n120: \n121: Check that Spec Kit Memory tools are available:\n122: \n123: ```json\n124: {\n125:   \"tool\": \"memory_health\",\n126:   \"arguments\": { \"reportMode\": \"full\" }\n127: }\n128: ```\n129: \n130: The response should return `status: \"ok\"` and database table counts. If it returns an error, see [Troubleshooting](#7-troubleshooting).\n131: \n132: Codex CLI note: if the MCP server runs in a restricted or read-only repo context, point `SPEC_KIT_DB_DIR` at a writable directory such as one under your home folder or `/tmp`. Use `MEMORY_DB_PATH` only when you intentionally need one fixed sqlite file.\n133: \n134: ---\n135: \n136: ## 4. FEATURES\n137: \n138: ### 4.1 SPEC FOLDER WORKFLOWS\n139: \n140: #### What Spec Folders Are\n141: \n142: A spec folder is a numbered directory (like `specs/042-my-feature/`) that holds the documentation for a single unit of work. Think of it as a project folder for an AI conversation. It keeps the specification, plan, task list and implementation summary together so the reasoning behind every change is preserved. For packet roots and direct child phases, closeout can also produce packet-local changelog entries that live beside the packet instead of only in the global release stream.\n143: \n144: Every conversation that modifies files gets a spec folder. This is enforced by Gate 3 in the project's AGENTS.md. The AI assistant asks \"Which spec folder?\" before any file modification begins. The only exemptions are single-file fixes under 5 characters (typo or whitespace corrections).\n145: \n146: #### Documentation Levels\n147: \n148: Not every change needs the same amount of paperwork. A one-line bug fix does not need an architecture decision record. A multi-system refactor does. Spec Kit uses four levels to match documentation depth to task complexity.\n149: \n150: | Level  | LOC Guidance   | Required Files                                        | When to Use                                          |\n151: | ------ | -------------- | ----------------------------------------------------- | ---------------------------------------------------- |\n152: | **1**  | < 100          | spec.md, plan.md, tasks.md, implementation-summary.md | Small features, bug fixes, single-file changes       |\n153: | **2**  | 100 - 499      | Level 1 + checklist.md                                | Features needing QA verification, multi-file changes |\n154: | **3**  | 500+           | Level 2 + decision-record.md                          | Architecture changes, complex refactors              |\n155: | **3+** | Complexity 80+ | Level 3 + approval workflow, compliance, stakeholders  | High-complexity work needing review tracking          |\n156: | **Phase Parent** | n/a (control file only) | spec.md, description.json, graph-metadata.json | Folder contains phase children (`[0-9]{3}-name/` subdirs with their own spec.md/description.json) |\n157: \n158: The LOC ranges are guidance, not hard rules. Risk, complexity and the number of affected files can push a task to a higher level. When in doubt, choose the higher level.\n159: \n160: **Implementation-summary.md** is required at all levels but created **after** implementation completes, not at spec folder creation time.\n161: \n162: Packet-local changelogs are additive, not a replacement for `implementation-summary.md`. When the target is a packet root or direct child phase, `/speckit:implement`, `/speckit:complete` and the nested changelog workflow can write packet history into a local `changelog/` directory using the canonical root/phase naming rules.\n163: \n164: #### Spec Folder Structure\n165: \n166: When `create.sh` builds a spec folder, it produces this layout:\n167: \n168: ```text\n169: specs/<###-feature-name>/\n170: ├── description.json             # Spec identity and memory tracking metadata\n171: ├── spec.md                      # What the feature is and why it exists\n172: ├── plan.md                      # How to implement it\n173: ├── tasks.md                     # Step-by-step task breakdown\n174: ├── checklist.md                 # QA validation gates (Level 2+)\n175: ├── decision-record.md           # Architecture decisions (Level 3+)\n176: ├── implementation-summary.md    # Post-implementation summary (all levels)\n177: ├── handover.md                  # Operator-facing session handoff for /speckit:resume\n178: ├── resource-map.md              # Optional lean path catalog (any level)\n179: ├── changelog/                   # Packet-local changelog history for packet roots / phase parents\n180: └── scratch/                     # Temporary workspace files (gitignored)\n181: ```\n182: \n183: `generate-context.js` updates the packet's continuity state for `/speckit:resume`, refreshes `description.json.lastUpdated` and rewrites `graph-metadata.json` derived fields on every canonical save. Recovery then rebuilds context from `handover.md`, `_memory.continuity` and the packet docs.\n184: \n185: **Phase parents** are an exception. When a folder contains phase children (matching `^[0-9]{3}-[a-z0-9-]+$` with their own `spec.md` or `description.json`), the parent only requires the **lean trio**: `spec.md`, `description.json`, `graph-metadata.json`. Heavy docs (`plan.md`, `tasks.md`, `checklist.md`, `decision-record.md`, `implementation-summary.md`) live exclusively in the children where they stay accurate to that phase's actual work. The parent's `spec.md` carries a Phase Documentation Map. The parent's `graph-metadata.json` carries `derived.last_active_child_id` + `derived.last_active_at` pointer fields that the generator atomically updates on every save (parent saves write `null`, child saves bubble up the child's `packet_id`). `/speckit:resume` reads the pointer first when the target is a phase parent. A fresh pointer (<24h) recurses directly into the active child. A stale or missing pointer falls back to listing children with statuses. Detection is a single source of truth: `is_phase_parent()` (shell) and `isPhaseParent()` (ESM JS) MUST agree.\n186: \n187: #### Checklist Priority System (Level 2+)\n188: \n189: Checklists use a priority system so reviewers know what blocks shipping and what can wait:\n190: \n191: | Priority | Meaning                                                 | Deferral                        |\n192: | -------- | ------------------------------------------------------- | ------------------------------- |\n193: | **P0**   | Hard blocker, cannot ship without this                | Cannot defer                    |\n194: | **P1**   | Required, must complete or get user approval to defer | Needs explicit approval to skip |\n195: | **P2**   | Optional, nice to have                                | Can defer without approval      |\n196: \n197: #### Phase Decomposition\n198: \n199: When a feature is too large for a single spec folder, use phase decomposition to split it into parent and child folders. The parent holds the overall specification. Each child holds one phase of the work.\n\n(Showing lines 90-199 of 1067. Use offset=200 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"\nStart a new session on work you did before:\n\n```text\n/speckit:resume\n```\n\nThe system rebuilds continuation context in a fixed order: `handover.md` first, then `_memory.continuity`, then the packet's canonical spec docs. It presents the current state, prior decisions, touched files and next steps before you start.\n\n### Search for Context\n\nAsk the indexed-continuity store a question in plain language:\n\n```text\n/memory:search \"how did we decide on the auth architecture?\"\n```\n\nThe system reads your question, figures out you are looking for a past decision and routes to the right search strategy automatically.\n\n### Validate a Spec Folder","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/README.md","text":"\nStart a new session on work you did before:\n\n```text\n/speckit:resume\n```\n\nThe system rebuilds continuation context in a fixed order: `handover.md` first, then `_memory.continuity`, then the packet's canonical spec docs. It presents the current state, prior decisions, touched files and next steps before you start.\n\n### Search for Context\n\nAsk the indexed-continuity store a question in plain language:\n\n```text\n/memory:search \"how did we decide on the auth architecture?\"\n```\n\nThe system reads your question, figures out you are looking for a past decision and routes to the right search strategy automatically.\n\n### Validate a Spec Folder\n\n```bash\n# Run all 20 validation rules\nbash .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/spec/validate.sh \\\n  .opencode/specs/[project]/042-my-feature/\n\n# Exit 0 = success, Exit 1 = user error, Exit 2 = validation error, Exit 3 = system error\n```\n\n### Verify the MCP Is Running\n\nCheck that Spec Kit Memory tools are available:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"tool\": \"memory_health\",\n  \"arguments\": { \"reportMode\": \"full\" }\n}\n```\n\nThe response should return `status: \"ok\"` and database table counts. If it returns an error, see [Troubleshooting](#7-troubleshooting).\n\nCodex CLI note: if the MCP server runs in a restricted or read-only repo context, point `SPEC_KIT_DB_DIR` at a writable directory such as one under your home folder or `/tmp`. Use `MEMORY_DB_PATH` only when you intentionally need one fixed sqlite file.\n\n---\n\n## 4. FEATURES\n\n### 4.1 SPEC FOLDER WORKFLOWS\n\n#### What Spec Folders Are\n\nA spec folder is a numbered directory (like `specs/042-my-feature/`) that holds the documentation for a single unit of work. Think of it as a project folder for an AI conversation. It keeps the specification, plan, task list and implementation summary together so the reasoning behind every change is preserved. For packet roots and direct child phases, closeout can also produce packet-local changelog entries that live beside the packet instead of only in the global release stream.\n\nEvery conversation that modifies files gets a spec folder. This is enforced by Gate 3 in the project's AGENTS.md. The AI assistant asks \"Which spec folder?\" before any file modification begins. The only exemptions are single-file fixes under 5 characters (typo or whitespace corrections).\n\n#### Documentation Levels\n\nNot every change needs the same amount of paperwork. A one-line bug fix does not need an architecture decision record. A multi-system refactor does. Spec Kit uses four levels to match documentation depth to task complexity.\n\n| Level  | LOC Guidance   | Required Files                                        | When to Use                                          |\n| ------ | -------------- | ----------------------------------------------------- | ---------------------------------------------------- |\n| **1**  | < 100          | spec.md, plan.md, tasks.md, implementation-summary.md | Small features, bug fixes, single-file changes       |\n| **2**  | 100 - 499      | Level 1 + checklist.md                                | Features needing QA verification, multi-file changes |\n| **3**  | 500+           | Level 2 + decision-record.md                          | Architecture changes, complex refactors              |\n| **3+** | Complexity 80+ | Level 3 + approval workflow, compliance, stakeholders  | High-complexity work needing review tracking          |\n| **Phase Parent** | n/a (control file only) | spec.md, description.json, graph-metadata.json | Folder contains phase children (`[0-9]{3}-name/` subdirs with their own spec.md/description.json) |\n\nThe LOC ranges are guidance, not hard rules. Risk, complexity and the number of affected files can push a task to a higher level. When in doubt, choose the higher level.\n\n**Implementation-summary.md** is required at all levels but created **after** implementation completes, not at spec folder creation time.\n\nPacket-local changelogs are additive, not a replacement for `implementation-summary.md`. When the target is a packet root or direct child phase, `/speckit:implement`, `/speckit:complete` and the nested changelog workflow can write packet history into a local `changelog/` directory using the canonical root/phase naming rules.\n\n#### Spec Folder Structure\n\nWhen `create.sh` builds a spec folder, it produces this layout:\n\n```text\nspecs/<###-feature-name>/\n├── description.json             # Spec identity and memory tracking metadata\n├── spec.md                      # What the feature is and why it exists\n├── plan.md                      # How to implement it\n├── tasks.md                     # Step-by-step task breakdown\n├── checklist.md                 # QA validation gates (Level 2+)\n├── decision-record.md           # Architecture decisions (Level 3+)\n├── implementation-summary.md    # Post-implementation summary (all levels)\n├── handover.md                  # Operator-facing session handoff for /speckit:resume\n├── resource-map.md              # Optional lean path catalog (any level)\n├── changelog/                   # Packet-local changelog history for packet roots / phase parents\n└── scratch/                     # Temporary workspace files (gitignored)\n```\n\n`generate-context.js` updates the packet's continuity state for `/speckit:resume`, refreshes `description.json.lastUpdated` and rewrites `graph-metadata.json` derived fields on every canonical save. Recovery then rebuilds context from `handover.md`, `_memory.continuity` and the packet docs.\n\n**Phase parents** are an exception. When a folder contains phase children (matching `^[0-9]{3}-[a-z0-9-]+$` with their own `spec.md` or `description.json`), the parent only requires the **lean trio**: `spec.md`, `description.json`, `graph-metadata.json`. Heavy docs (`plan.md`, `tasks.md`, `checklist.md`, `decision-record.md`, `implementation-summary.md`) live exclusively in the children where they stay accurate to that phase's actual work. The parent's `spec.md` carries a Phase Documentation Map. The parent's `graph-metadata.json` carries `derived.last_active_child_id` + `derived.last_active_at` pointer fields that the generator atomically updates on every save (parent saves write `null`, child saves bubble up the child's `packet_id`). `/speckit:resume` reads the pointer first when the target is a phase parent. A fresh pointer (<24h) recurses directly into the active child. A stale or missing pointer falls back to listing children with statuses. Detection is a single source of truth: `is_phase_parent()` (shell) and `isPhaseParent()` (ESM JS) MUST agree.\n\n#### Checklist Priority System (Level 2+)\n\nChecklists use a priority system so reviewers know what blocks shipping and what can wait:\n\n| Priority | Meaning                                                 | Deferral                        |\n| -------- | ------------------------------------------------------- | ------------------------------- |\n| **P0**   | Hard blocker, cannot ship without this                | Cannot defer                    |\n| **P1**   | Required, must complete or get user approval to defer | Needs explicit approval to skip |\n| **P2**   | Optional, nice to have                                | Can defer without approval      |\n\n#### Phase Decomposition\n\nWhen a feature is too large for a single spec folder, use phase decomposition to split it into parent and child folders. The parent holds the overall specification. Each child holds one phase of the work.","lineStart":90,"lineEnd":199,"totalLines":1067,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/README.md","time":{"start":1780925357702,"end":1780925357722}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0f5bcb161580130a016a26c3ad9d10819185c976e49818353c"}},"id":"prt_ea76c5e7e00140Heb6FicV5cB7","sessionID":"ses_158954ac7ffeX00Y2fH37dXkNJ","messageID":"msg_ea76c3e63001uhwXOldtDAOrVn"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780925357740,"sessionID":"ses_158954ac7ffeX00Y2fH37dXkNJ","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_h8ByBu5H9NwL07k01iQeqdud","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/config/hook_system.md","offset":1,"limit":260},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/config/hook_system.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: Hook System Reference\n3: description: Current hook registration, runtime vocabulary, lifecycle behavior, and fallback contracts for Spec Kit prompt-time and session hooks.\n4: ---\n5: \n6: # Hook System Reference\n7: \n8: Current hook registration, runtime vocabulary, lifecycle behavior, and fallback contracts for Spec Kit prompt-time and session hooks.\n9: \n10: ---\n11: \n12: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n13: \n14: The hook system provides automated context preservation at hook-capable prompt-time and lifecycle boundaries. Prompt delivery, startup wiring, compaction, and shutdown handling differ by runtime, but they call the same retrieval primitives and fail open to the same operator recovery path.\n15: \n16: ---\n17: \n18: ## 2. HOOK REGISTRATION\n19: \n20: Claude Code hooks are registered in `.claude/settings.local.json`. Under the normalized Claude schema, `UserPromptSubmit` is the prompt hook, while `PreCompact`, `SessionStart`, and `Stop` are lifecycle hooks:\n21: \n22: ```json\n23: {\n24:   \"hooks\": {\n25:     \"UserPromptSubmit\": [{ \"hooks\": [{ \"type\": \"command\", \"command\": \"node .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/dist/hooks/claude/user-prompt-submit.js\", \"timeout\": 3 }] }],\n26:     \"PreCompact\": [{ \"hooks\": [{ \"type\": \"command\", \"command\": \"node .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/dist/hooks/claude/compact-inject.js\", \"timeout\": 3 }] }],\n27:     \"SessionStart\": [{ \"hooks\": [{ \"type\": \"command\", \"command\": \"node .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/dist/hooks/claude/session-prime.js\", \"timeout\": 3 }] }],\n28:     \"Stop\": [{ \"hooks\": [{ \"type\": \"command\", \"command\": \"node .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/dist/hooks/claude/session-stop.js\", \"async\": true, \"timeout\": 10 }] }]\n29:   }\n30: }\n31: ```\n32: \n33: Copilot registration is owned by the Copilot-local README at `mcp_server/hooks/copilot/README.md`. Copilot does not use the Claude Code `.claude/settings.local.json` nested hook block and must not add top-level `type`, `bash`, or `timeoutSec` wrapper fields there. The current Copilot path runs Copilot-supported writer scripts, including the checked-in `.github/hooks/superset-notify.json` wrapper where available, and refreshes the managed custom-instructions block for the next prompt. Copilot advisor freshness is NEXT-PROMPT: the current prompt sees the PRIOR turn's brief.\n34: \n35: Codex registration is owned by the user/workspace Codex runtime config, not by the repo template alone. The checked-in `.codex/settings.json` is an example hook template for the project commands. Live native Codex readiness requires `[features].codex_hooks = true` in `~/.codex/config.toml` or an equivalent `--enable codex_hooks` launch flag, plus `~/.codex/hooks.json` or workspace `hooks.json` registration for the compiled Spec Kit hooks.\n36: \n37: ### Codex Hook Contract Versions\n38: \n39: | Contract | Date / version note | Registration point | Trigger | Status |\n40: | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n41: | Legacy repo template | Retained for repo examples and local policy shape | `.codex/settings.json` | None by itself; copy/adapt into live Codex hook registration | Example only |\n42: | Current native hook contract | Active runtime contract as of 2026-04-29 | `~/.codex/config.toml` with `[features].codex_hooks = true` plus `~/.codex/hooks.json` or workspace `hooks.json` | Codex `SessionStart`, `UserPromptSubmit`, and optional `PreToolUse` native hooks | Authoritative live registration |\n43: | Fallback prompt wrapper | Compatibility behavior | `hooks/codex/prompt-wrapper.ts` when native hook readiness reports unavailable | Explicit wrapper invocation | Fallback, not native hook registration |\n44: \n45: ---\n46: \n47: ## 3. CANONICAL RUNTIME HOOK VOCABULARY\n48: \n49: Use support names first, then map to the runtime-local surface below when wiring or validating a specific runtime:\n50: \n51: | Support | Claude / Codex / Copilot | Gemini | OpenCode | Trigger / fallback |\n52: | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n53: | Prompt-time advisor | `UserPromptSubmit` | `BeforeAgent` | `experimental.chat.system.transform` | Runtime prompt hook; Copilot is NEXT-PROMPT freshness, so current prompt sees PRIOR turn's brief; fallback is explicit `skill_advisor.py` or advisor MCP tooling |\n54: | Session priming | `SessionStart` | `SessionStart` | `event` startup handlers | Runtime startup hook; fallback is `/spec_kit:resume` or `session_bootstrap()` |\n55: | Compaction | `PreCompact` | `PreCompress` plus `BeforeAgent` injection | `event` compact handlers / compact plugin | Runtime compaction event; fallback is resume ladder |\n56: | Session cleanup | `Stop` | `SessionEnd` | `event` cleanup handlers | Runtime session-end event where supported; fallback is `/memory:save` |\n57: \n58: ---\n59: \n60: ## 4. HOOK LIFECYCLE\n61: \n62: 1. **Prompt-time advisor** — `UserPromptSubmit` in Claude, Codex, and Copilot; `BeforeAgent` in Gemini; `experimental.chat.system.transform` in OpenCode. Claude, Gemini, Codex, and OpenCode can inject runtime-visible advisor context in-turn. Copilot uses the same logical surface to refresh managed custom instructions and returns `{}`; this is NEXT-PROMPT freshness, so the current prompt sees the PRIOR turn's brief.\n63: 2. **Compaction** — `PreCompact` in Claude, `PreCompress` plus `BeforeAgent` reinjection in Gemini, compact `event` handlers in OpenCode, and limited wrapper-only parity in Copilot. Stdout is not injected on the precompute phase.\n64: 3. **SessionStart** — Fires on session start. Routes by source:\n65:    - `compact`: Reads cached PreCompact payload, injects via stdout\n66:    - `startup`: Primes with Spec Kit Memory overview\n67:    - `resume`: Loads prior session state — respects the phase-parent pointer redirect documented in `references/hooks/skill_advisor_hook.md`. When the resume target is a phase parent and `derived.last_active_child_id` is fresh (<24h), priming surfaces the active child rather than the parent's listing\n68:    - `clear`: Minimal output\n69:    Gemini and Copilot keep runtime-specific transport output, but both can forward the same session and spec-folder startup scope used by Claude when that input is available. Codex only reports live native-hook readiness when `[features].codex_hooks = true` is enabled in `~/.codex/config.toml` or equivalent launch flags and a user/workspace `hooks.json` is wired. Repo `.codex/settings.json` is a template/example, not the live readiness predicate.\n70: 4. **Session cleanup** — `Stop` in Claude, `SessionEnd` in Gemini, and cleanup `event` handlers in OpenCode. Parses transcript JSONL for token usage, calculates cost estimates, and stores snapshots when the runtime supports it.\n71: \n72: ---\n73: \n74: ## 5. HOOK STATE\n75: \n76: Per-session state stored at `${os.tmpdir()}/speckit-claude-hooks/<project-hash>/<session-id>.json`.\n77: \n78: Fields: `claudeSessionId`, `speckitSessionId`, `lastSpecFolder`, `pendingCompactPrime`, `metrics` (prompt/completion tokens, transcript offset).\n79: \n80: ---\n81: \n82: ## 6. SCRIPT LOCATIONS\n83: \n84: Source: `mcp_server/hooks/claude/*.ts`\n85: Compiled: `mcp_server/dist/hooks/claude/*.js`\n86: \n87: ---\n88: \n89: ## 7. TOKEN BUDGETS\n90: \n91: - Compaction injection: 4000 tokens (`COMPACTION_TOKEN_BUDGET`)\n92: - Session priming: 2000 tokens (`SESSION_PRIME_TOKEN_BUDGET`)\n93: - Hook timeout: 1800ms (`HOOK_TIMEOUT_MS`, under 2s hard cap)\n94: \n95: ---\n96: \n97: ## 8. RUNTIME HOOK MATRIX\n98: \n99: Prompt hooks and lifecycle hooks are separate support. A runtime can support prompt-time advisor context without supporting startup/code-graph lifecycle injection, and Copilot's prompt-time parity is NEXT-PROMPT freshness rather than in-turn injection; the current prompt sees the PRIOR turn's brief.\n100: \n101: | Runtime | Prompt hook | Lifecycle hook | Compaction | Stop | Trigger / default | Manual fallback |\n102: | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n103: | Claude | yes (`UserPromptSubmit`) | yes (`SessionStart`) | yes (`PreCompact`) | yes (`Stop`) | `.claude/settings.local.json` hook events | `/spec_kit:resume`, `/memory:save`, direct MCP tools |\n104: | Codex | yes (`UserPromptSubmit`) | yes (`SessionStart`, live only when `codex_hooks` and `hooks.json` are both present) | no | no Spec Kit cleanup hook | `[features].codex_hooks = true` plus user/workspace `hooks.json`; `.codex/settings.json` is template-only | `/spec_kit:resume`, `session_bootstrap()`, prompt-wrapper fallback |\n105: | Copilot | yes (file-based custom instructions; NEXT-PROMPT freshness; current prompt sees PRIOR turn's brief) | yes (`SessionStart` writer) | limited cache/writer path; no model-visible precompute injection | n/a | Copilot-supported writer scripts; see `mcp_server/hooks/copilot/README.md` | Managed instructions file or `/spec_kit:resume` |\n106: | Gemini | no checked-in project hook | no checked-in project hook | no checked-in project hook | no checked-in project hook | External CLI only | `/spec_kit:resume`, `/memory:save` |\n107: | OpenCode | yes (`experimental.chat.system.transform`) | yes (`event` startup handlers) | yes (`event` compact handlers / compact plugin) | yes (`event` cleanup handlers) | Plugin bridge and event handlers | `/spec_kit:resume`, direct MCP tools |\n108: \n109: ### Codex Timeout Fallback Semantics\n110: \n111: Codex `UserPromptSubmit` uses `SPECKIT_CODEX_HOOK_TIMEOUT_MS` (default `3000`) for the advisor builder. If the builder times out, the hook returns prompt-safe stale context with a machine-visible marker: `stale: true`, `reason: \"timeout-fallback\"`. The hook also writes one structured warning line (`event: \"codex_user_prompt_timeout_fallback\"`) before its normal prompt-safe diagnostic. Operators can run the smoke helper in `hooks/codex/lib/freshness-smoke-check.ts` to check cold-start freshness (`fresh`, `lastUpdateAt`, `latencyMs`) before adjusting timeout values.\n112: \n113: ---\n114: \n115: ## 9. CROSS-RUNTIME FALLBACK\n116: \n117: Claude Code uses native `UserPromptSubmit`, `SessionStart`, `PreCompact`, and `Stop` hooks. Gemini CLI uses native `BeforeAgent`, `SessionStart`, `PreCompress`, and `SessionEnd` hooks. Copilot CLI uses Copilot-supported writer scripts that refresh the Spec Kit managed block in `$HOME/.copilot/copilot-instructions.md`; hook output remains `{}` with NEXT-PROMPT freshness semantics, so the current prompt sees the PRIOR turn's brief, and the registration contract is documented in `mcp_server/hooks/copilot/README.md`. Do not use the stale merged `.claude/settings.local.json` wrapper shape for Copilot. OpenCode uses plugin-based transport rather than shell wrappers: `.opencode/plugins/mk-skill-advisor.js` delivers prompt-time advisor briefs through `experimental.chat.system.transform`, while `.opencode/plugins/mk-code-graph.js` and plugin `event` handlers cover startup, compaction, readiness, and session cleanup. Codex CLI only reports live native-hook readiness when `[features].codex_hooks = true` is enabled in `~/.codex/config.toml` or equivalent launch flags and user/workspace `hooks.json` is wired; on `UserPromptSubmit` timeout, Codex returns a stale fallback marker (`stale:true`, `reason:\"timeout-fallback\"`) and logs a structured warning instead of silently serving cold-start context. Use `/spec_kit:resume` when hooks are unavailable or disabled. If automatic hook delivery is unavailable in any runtime, or the advisor hook path is intentionally disabled (`SPECKIT_SKILL_ADVISOR_HOOK_DISABLED=1`), fall back to the canonical operator path: start with `/spec_kit:resume`, rebuild packet continuity from `handover.md -> _memory.continuity -> spec docs`, then use `session_bootstrap()` or `session_resume()` only when you need lower-level structural health or merged recovery detail.\n118: \n119: ---\n120: \n121: ## 10. SHARED STARTUP PAYLOAD PARITY\n122: \n123: All four supported runtimes transport the same compact startup shared-payload through their runtime-specific hooks. The payload is produced by `buildStartupBrief()`, which is defined locally in each runtime's session-prime hook and delegates to `getStartupBriefFromMarker()` in `mcp_server/lib/code-graph-boundary.ts`; it includes `graphQualitySummary` (detector provenance + edge-enrichment summary) alongside the `sharedPayloadTransport` envelope. Runtime-specific startup entrypoints:\n124: \n125: | Runtime | Startup entrypoint | Transport | Trigger |\n126: | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n127: | Claude | `hooks/claude/session-prime.ts` | stdout context injection | Claude `SessionStart` |\n128: | Gemini | `hooks/gemini/session-prime.ts` | SessionStart injection | Gemini `SessionStart` |\n129: | Copilot | `hooks/copilot/session-prime.ts` | refreshes managed block in `$HOME/.copilot/copilot-instructions.md` | Copilot-supported writer script; next prompt observes the block |\n130: | Codex | `hooks/codex/session-start.ts` | native `SessionStart` hook | `[features].codex_hooks = true` plus user/workspace `hooks.json` |\n131: \n132: `graphQualitySummary` is also surfaced on `code_graph_status` and `session_bootstrap()` / startup-brief responses, so operators can inspect the same quality envelope regardless of transport. `session_bootstrap()` remains a manual fallback when native startup hooks are disabled — it is no longer a Codex-only substitute.\n133: \n134: Hooks remain in `system-spec-kit` because they own runtime lifecycle transport. Code-graph readiness, quality, and package docs are owned by the sibling `.opencode/skills/system-code-graph/` skill and imported through the co-resident MCP registration path.\n135: \n136: ---\n137: \n138: ## 11. ADVISOR BRIDGE AND THRESHOLD CONTRACT\n139: \n140: OpenCode delivers prompt-time advisor context through a plugin-helper bridge rather than a shell wrapper:\n141: \n142: - Plugin: `.opencode/plugins/mk-skill-advisor.js`\n143: - Bridge entrypoint: `.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/plugin_bridges/mk-skill-advisor-bridge.mjs`\n144: - Target: native compat entrypoint under `.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/compat/`\n145: \n146: The bridge routes through the shared `renderAdvisorBrief(...)` invariants used by the Codex prompt-submit hook and prompt-wrapper fallback. The default OpenCode prompt-time threshold contract is **`0.8` confidence / `0.35` uncertainty**.\n147: \n148: The public MCP contract is unified across runtime hook surfaces:\n149: \n150: - `advisor_recommend` and `advisor_validate` accept an explicit `workspaceRoot` argument; both responses surface the resolved `workspaceRoot` and `effectiveThresholds` used for routing.\n151: - `advisor_status` is diagnostic-only and does not rebuild. Use `advisor_rebuild({})` when status reports stale/absent/unavailable, or `advisor_rebuild({\"force\":true})` for an explicit live-state rebuild.\n152: - `advisor_validate` additionally publishes `thresholdSemantics` (aggregate vs runtime) plus a prompt-safe `telemetry.outcomes.totals` block (`accepted` / `corrected` / `ignored`).\n153: - Hook diagnostics persist to bounded JSONL sinks under the temp metrics root (`${TMPDIR}/speckit-advisor-metrics/`), so `advisor_validate` can read the sinks back across processes.\n154: \n155: ---\n156: \n157: ## 12. RETRIEVAL PRIMITIVES\n158: \n159: The same retrieval building blocks power both hook delivery and explicit recovery:\n160: 1. `memory_match_triggers(prompt)` — Fast turn-start context\n161: 2. `memory_context({ mode: \"resume\", profile: \"resume\" })` — Continuation and compaction recovery core\n162: 3. `session_bootstrap()` / `session_resume()` — Session-oriented wrappers that layer health and structural context around resume retrieval\n163: \n164: ---\n\n(End of file - total 164 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: Hook System Reference\ndescription: Current hook registration, runtime vocabulary, lifecycle behavior, and fallback contracts for Spec Kit prompt-time and session hooks.\n---\n\n# Hook System Reference\n\nCurrent hook registration, runtime vocabulary, lifecycle behavior, and fallback contracts for Spec Kit prompt-time and session hooks.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\nThe hook system provides automated context preservation at hook-capable prompt-time and lifecycle boundaries. Prompt delivery, startup wiring, compaction, and shutdown handling differ by runtime, but they call the same retrieval primitives and fail open to the same operator recovery path.\n\n---\n\n## 2. HOOK REGISTRATION\n\nClaude Code hooks are registered in `.claude/settings.local.json`. Under the normalized Claude schema, `UserPromptSubmit` is the prompt hook, while `PreCompact`, `SessionStart`, and `Stop` are lifecycle hooks:","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/config/hook_system.md","text":"---\ntitle: Hook System Reference\ndescription: Current hook registration, runtime vocabulary, lifecycle behavior, and fallback contracts for Spec Kit prompt-time and session hooks.\n---\n\n# Hook System Reference\n\nCurrent hook registration, runtime vocabulary, lifecycle behavior, and fallback contracts for Spec Kit prompt-time and session hooks.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\nThe hook system provides automated context preservation at hook-capable prompt-time and lifecycle boundaries. Prompt delivery, startup wiring, compaction, and shutdown handling differ by runtime, but they call the same retrieval primitives and fail open to the same operator recovery path.\n\n---\n\n## 2. HOOK REGISTRATION\n\nClaude Code hooks are registered in `.claude/settings.local.json`. Under the normalized Claude schema, `UserPromptSubmit` is the prompt hook, while `PreCompact`, `SessionStart`, and `Stop` are lifecycle hooks:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"hooks\": {\n    \"UserPromptSubmit\": [{ \"hooks\": [{ \"type\": \"command\", \"command\": \"node .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/dist/hooks/claude/user-prompt-submit.js\", \"timeout\": 3 }] }],\n    \"PreCompact\": [{ \"hooks\": [{ \"type\": \"command\", \"command\": \"node .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/dist/hooks/claude/compact-inject.js\", \"timeout\": 3 }] }],\n    \"SessionStart\": [{ \"hooks\": [{ \"type\": \"command\", \"command\": \"node .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/dist/hooks/claude/session-prime.js\", \"timeout\": 3 }] }],\n    \"Stop\": [{ \"hooks\": [{ \"type\": \"command\", \"command\": \"node .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/dist/hooks/claude/session-stop.js\", \"async\": true, \"timeout\": 10 }] }]\n  }\n}\n```\n\nCopilot registration is owned by the Copilot-local README at `mcp_server/hooks/copilot/README.md`. Copilot does not use the Claude Code `.claude/settings.local.json` nested hook block and must not add top-level `type`, `bash`, or `timeoutSec` wrapper fields there. The current Copilot path runs Copilot-supported writer scripts, including the checked-in `.github/hooks/superset-notify.json` wrapper where available, and refreshes the managed custom-instructions block for the next prompt. Copilot advisor freshness is NEXT-PROMPT: the current prompt sees the PRIOR turn's brief.\n\nCodex registration is owned by the user/workspace Codex runtime config, not by the repo template alone. The checked-in `.codex/settings.json` is an example hook template for the project commands. Live native Codex readiness requires `[features].codex_hooks = true` in `~/.codex/config.toml` or an equivalent `--enable codex_hooks` launch flag, plus `~/.codex/hooks.json` or workspace `hooks.json` registration for the compiled Spec Kit hooks.\n\n### Codex Hook Contract Versions\n\n| Contract | Date / version note | Registration point | Trigger | Status |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| Legacy repo template | Retained for repo examples and local policy shape | `.codex/settings.json` | None by itself; copy/adapt into live Codex hook registration | Example only |\n| Current native hook contract | Active runtime contract as of 2026-04-29 | `~/.codex/config.toml` with `[features].codex_hooks = true` plus `~/.codex/hooks.json` or workspace `hooks.json` | Codex `SessionStart`, `UserPromptSubmit`, and optional `PreToolUse` native hooks | Authoritative live registration |\n| Fallback prompt wrapper | Compatibility behavior | `hooks/codex/prompt-wrapper.ts` when native hook readiness reports unavailable | Explicit wrapper invocation | Fallback, not native hook registration |\n\n---\n\n## 3. CANONICAL RUNTIME HOOK VOCABULARY\n\nUse support names first, then map to the runtime-local surface below when wiring or validating a specific runtime:\n\n| Support | Claude / Codex / Copilot | Gemini | OpenCode | Trigger / fallback |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| Prompt-time advisor | `UserPromptSubmit` | `BeforeAgent` | `experimental.chat.system.transform` | Runtime prompt hook; Copilot is NEXT-PROMPT freshness, so current prompt sees PRIOR turn's brief; fallback is explicit `skill_advisor.py` or advisor MCP tooling |\n| Session priming | `SessionStart` | `SessionStart` | `event` startup handlers | Runtime startup hook; fallback is `/spec_kit:resume` or `session_bootstrap()` |\n| Compaction | `PreCompact` | `PreCompress` plus `BeforeAgent` injection | `event` compact handlers / compact plugin | Runtime compaction event; fallback is resume ladder |\n| Session cleanup | `Stop` | `SessionEnd` | `event` cleanup handlers | Runtime session-end event where supported; fallback is `/memory:save` |\n\n---\n\n## 4. HOOK LIFECYCLE\n\n1. **Prompt-time advisor** — `UserPromptSubmit` in Claude, Codex, and Copilot; `BeforeAgent` in Gemini; `experimental.chat.system.transform` in OpenCode. Claude, Gemini, Codex, and OpenCode can inject runtime-visible advisor context in-turn. Copilot uses the same logical surface to refresh managed custom instructions and returns `{}`; this is NEXT-PROMPT freshness, so the current prompt sees the PRIOR turn's brief.\n2. **Compaction** — `PreCompact` in Claude, `PreCompress` plus `BeforeAgent` reinjection in Gemini, compact `event` handlers in OpenCode, and limited wrapper-only parity in Copilot. Stdout is not injected on the precompute phase.\n3. **SessionStart** — Fires on session start. Routes by source:\n   - `compact`: Reads cached PreCompact payload, injects via stdout\n   - `startup`: Primes with Spec Kit Memory overview\n   - `resume`: Loads prior session state — respects the phase-parent pointer redirect documented in `references/hooks/skill_advisor_hook.md`. When the resume target is a phase parent and `derived.last_active_child_id` is fresh (<24h), priming surfaces the active child rather than the parent's listing\n   - `clear`: Minimal output\n   Gemini and Copilot keep runtime-specific transport output, but both can forward the same session and spec-folder startup scope used by Claude when that input is available. Codex only reports live native-hook readiness when `[features].codex_hooks = true` is enabled in `~/.codex/config.toml` or equivalent launch flags and a user/workspace `hooks.json` is wired. Repo `.codex/settings.json` is a template/example, not the live readiness predicate.\n4. **Session cleanup** — `Stop` in Claude, `SessionEnd` in Gemini, and cleanup `event` handlers in OpenCode. Parses transcript JSONL for token usage, calculates cost estimates, and stores snapshots when the runtime supports it.\n\n---\n\n## 5. HOOK STATE\n\nPer-session state stored at `${os.tmpdir()}/speckit-claude-hooks/<project-hash>/<session-id>.json`.\n\nFields: `claudeSessionId`, `speckitSessionId`, `lastSpecFolder`, `pendingCompactPrime`, `metrics` (prompt/completion tokens, transcript offset).\n\n---\n\n## 6. SCRIPT LOCATIONS\n\nSource: `mcp_server/hooks/claude/*.ts`\nCompiled: `mcp_server/dist/hooks/claude/*.js`\n\n---\n\n## 7. TOKEN BUDGETS\n\n- Compaction injection: 4000 tokens (`COMPACTION_TOKEN_BUDGET`)\n- Session priming: 2000 tokens (`SESSION_PRIME_TOKEN_BUDGET`)\n- Hook timeout: 1800ms (`HOOK_TIMEOUT_MS`, under 2s hard cap)\n\n---\n\n## 8. RUNTIME HOOK MATRIX\n\nPrompt hooks and lifecycle hooks are separate support. A runtime can support prompt-time advisor context without supporting startup/code-graph lifecycle injection, and Copilot's prompt-time parity is NEXT-PROMPT freshness rather than in-turn injection; the current prompt sees the PRIOR turn's brief.\n\n| Runtime | Prompt hook | Lifecycle hook | Compaction | Stop | Trigger / default | Manual fallback |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| Claude | yes (`UserPromptSubmit`) | yes (`SessionStart`) | yes (`PreCompact`) | yes (`Stop`) | `.claude/settings.local.json` hook events | `/spec_kit:resume`, `/memory:save`, direct MCP tools |\n| Codex | yes (`UserPromptSubmit`) | yes (`SessionStart`, live only when `codex_hooks` and `hooks.json` are both present) | no | no Spec Kit cleanup hook | `[features].codex_hooks = true` plus user/workspace `hooks.json`; `.codex/settings.json` is template-only | `/spec_kit:resume`, `session_bootstrap()`, prompt-wrapper fallback |\n| Copilot | yes (file-based custom instructions; NEXT-PROMPT freshness; current prompt sees PRIOR turn's brief) | yes (`SessionStart` writer) | limited cache/writer path; no model-visible precompute injection | n/a | Copilot-supported writer scripts; see `mcp_server/hooks/copilot/README.md` | Managed instructions file or `/spec_kit:resume` |\n| Gemini | no checked-in project hook | no checked-in project hook | no checked-in project hook | no checked-in project hook | External CLI only | `/spec_kit:resume`, `/memory:save` |\n| OpenCode | yes (`experimental.chat.system.transform`) | yes (`event` startup handlers) | yes (`event` compact handlers / compact plugin) | yes (`event` cleanup handlers) | Plugin bridge and event handlers | `/spec_kit:resume`, direct MCP tools |\n\n### Codex Timeout Fallback Semantics\n\nCodex `UserPromptSubmit` uses `SPECKIT_CODEX_HOOK_TIMEOUT_MS` (default `3000`) for the advisor builder. If the builder times out, the hook returns prompt-safe stale context with a machine-visible marker: `stale: true`, `reason: \"timeout-fallback\"`. The hook also writes one structured warning line (`event: \"codex_user_prompt_timeout_fallback\"`) before its normal prompt-safe diagnostic. Operators can run the smoke helper in `hooks/codex/lib/freshness-smoke-check.ts` to check cold-start freshness (`fresh`, `lastUpdateAt`, `latencyMs`) before adjusting timeout values.\n\n---\n\n## 9. CROSS-RUNTIME FALLBACK\n\nClaude Code uses native `UserPromptSubmit`, `SessionStart`, `PreCompact`, and `Stop` hooks. Gemini CLI uses native `BeforeAgent`, `SessionStart`, `PreCompress`, and `SessionEnd` hooks. Copilot CLI uses Copilot-supported writer scripts that refresh the Spec Kit managed block in `$HOME/.copilot/copilot-instructions.md`; hook output remains `{}` with NEXT-PROMPT freshness semantics, so the current prompt sees the PRIOR turn's brief, and the registration contract is documented in `mcp_server/hooks/copilot/README.md`. Do not use the stale merged `.claude/settings.local.json` wrapper shape for Copilot. OpenCode uses plugin-based transport rather than shell wrappers: `.opencode/plugins/mk-skill-advisor.js` delivers prompt-time advisor briefs through `experimental.chat.system.transform`, while `.opencode/plugins/mk-code-graph.js` and plugin `event` handlers cover startup, compaction, readiness, and session cleanup. Codex CLI only reports live native-hook readiness when `[features].codex_hooks = true` is enabled in `~/.codex/config.toml` or equivalent launch flags and user/workspace `hooks.json` is wired; on `UserPromptSubmit` timeout, Codex returns a stale fallback marker (`stale:true`, `reason:\"timeout-fallback\"`) and logs a structured warning instead of silently serving cold-start context. Use `/spec_kit:resume` when hooks are unavailable or disabled. If automatic hook delivery is unavailable in any runtime, or the advisor hook path is intentionally disabled (`SPECKIT_SKILL_ADVISOR_HOOK_DISABLED=1`), fall back to the canonical operator path: start with `/spec_kit:resume`, rebuild packet continuity from `handover.md -> _memory.continuity -> spec docs`, then use `session_bootstrap()` or `session_resume()` only when you need lower-level structural health or merged recovery detail.\n\n---\n\n## 10. SHARED STARTUP PAYLOAD PARITY\n\nAll four supported runtimes transport the same compact startup shared-payload through their runtime-specific hooks. The payload is produced by `buildStartupBrief()`, which is defined locally in each runtime's session-prime hook and delegates to `getStartupBriefFromMarker()` in `mcp_server/lib/code-graph-boundary.ts`; it includes `graphQualitySummary` (detector provenance + edge-enrichment summary) alongside the `sharedPayloadTransport` envelope. Runtime-specific startup entrypoints:\n\n| Runtime | Startup entrypoint | Transport | Trigger |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| Claude | `hooks/claude/session-prime.ts` | stdout context injection | Claude `SessionStart` |\n| Gemini | `hooks/gemini/session-prime.ts` | SessionStart injection | Gemini `SessionStart` |\n| Copilot | `hooks/copilot/session-prime.ts` | refreshes managed block in `$HOME/.copilot/copilot-instructions.md` | Copilot-supported writer script; next prompt observes the block |\n| Codex | `hooks/codex/session-start.ts` | native `SessionStart` hook | `[features].codex_hooks = true` plus user/workspace `hooks.json` |\n\n`graphQualitySummary` is also surfaced on `code_graph_status` and `session_bootstrap()` / startup-brief responses, so operators can inspect the same quality envelope regardless of transport. `session_bootstrap()` remains a manual fallback when native startup hooks are disabled — it is no longer a Codex-only substitute.\n\nHooks remain in `system-spec-kit` because they own runtime lifecycle transport. Code-graph readiness, quality, and package docs are owned by the sibling `.opencode/skills/system-code-graph/` skill and imported through the co-resident MCP registration path.\n\n---\n\n## 11. ADVISOR BRIDGE AND THRESHOLD CONTRACT\n\nOpenCode delivers prompt-time advisor context through a plugin-helper bridge rather than a shell wrapper:\n\n- Plugin: `.opencode/plugins/mk-skill-advisor.js`\n- Bridge entrypoint: `.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/plugin_bridges/mk-skill-advisor-bridge.mjs`\n- Target: native compat entrypoint under `.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/compat/`\n\nThe bridge routes through the shared `renderAdvisorBrief(...)` invariants used by the Codex prompt-submit hook and prompt-wrapper fallback. The default OpenCode prompt-time threshold contract is **`0.8` confidence / `0.35` uncertainty**.\n\nThe public MCP contract is unified across runtime hook surfaces:\n\n- `advisor_recommend` and `advisor_validate` accept an explicit `workspaceRoot` argument; both responses surface the resolved `workspaceRoot` and `effectiveThresholds` used for routing.\n- `advisor_status` is diagnostic-only and does not rebuild. Use `advisor_rebuild({})` when status reports stale/absent/unavailable, or `advisor_rebuild({\"force\":true})` for an explicit live-state rebuild.\n- `advisor_validate` additionally publishes `thresholdSemantics` (aggregate vs runtime) plus a prompt-safe `telemetry.outcomes.totals` block (`accepted` / `corrected` / `ignored`).\n- Hook diagnostics persist to bounded JSONL sinks under the temp metrics root (`${TMPDIR}/speckit-advisor-metrics/`), so `advisor_validate` can read the sinks back across processes.\n\n---\n\n## 12. RETRIEVAL PRIMITIVES\n\nThe same retrieval building blocks power both hook delivery and explicit recovery:\n1. `memory_match_triggers(prompt)` — Fast turn-start context\n2. `memory_context({ mode: \"resume\", profile: \"resume\" })` — Continuation and compaction recovery core\n3. `session_bootstrap()` / `session_resume()` — Session-oriented wrappers that layer health and structural context around resume retrieval\n\n---","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":164,"totalLines":164,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/config/hook_system.md","time":{"start":1780925357707,"end":1780925357727}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0f5bcb161580130a016a26c3ad9d1c81919e9376e143629071"}},"id":"prt_ea76c5e88001tswyspw4o9MUpf","sessionID":"ses_158954ac7ffeX00Y2fH37dXkNJ","messageID":"msg_ea76c3e63001uhwXOldtDAOrVn"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780925357771,"sessionID":"ses_158954ac7ffeX00Y2fH37dXkNJ","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_kYaKNm11tHGLHnj4YDhgiCIq","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/hooks/claude/session-prime.ts","offset":1,"limit":260},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/hooks/claude/session-prime.ts</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: #!/usr/bin/env node\n2: // ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n3: // MODULE: SessionStart Hook — Session Prime\n4: // ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n5: // Runs on Claude Code SessionStart event. Injects context via stdout\n6: // based on the session source (compact, startup, resume, clear).\n7: \n8: import { resolve } from 'node:path';\n9: import { fileURLToPath } from 'node:url';\n10: import {\n11:   parseHookStdin, hookLog, formatHookOutput, truncateToTokenBudget,\n12:   withTimeout, HOOK_TIMEOUT_MS, COMPACTION_TOKEN_BUDGET, SESSION_PRIME_TOKEN_BUDGET,\n13:   calculatePressureAdjustedBudget, sanitizeRecoveredPayload, wrapRecoveredCompactPayload,\n14:   getRequiredSessionId,\n15:   type HookInput,\n16:   type OutputSection,\n17: } from './shared.js';\n18: import {\n19:   ensureStateDir,\n20:   loadState,\n21:   readCompactPrime,\n22:   clearCompactPrime,\n23:   validatePendingCompactPrimeSemantics,\n24: } from './hook-state.js';\n25: import { getCachedSessionSummaryDecision, logCachedSummaryDecision } from '../../handlers/session-resume.js';\n26: import { getStartupBriefFromMarker } from '../../lib/code-graph-boundary.js';\n27: \n28: const CACHE_TTL_MS = 30 * 60 * 1000;\n29: const IS_CLI_ENTRY = process.argv[1]\n30:   ? resolve(process.argv[1]) === fileURLToPath(import.meta.url)\n31:   : false;\n32: type StartupBrief = {\n33:   graphOutline: string | null;\n34:   sessionContinuity: string | null;\n35:   graphSummary: { files: number; nodes: number; edges: number; lastScan: string | null } | null;\n36:   graphQualitySummary?: unknown;\n37:   graphState: 'ready' | 'stale' | 'empty' | 'missing';\n38:   startupSurface: string;\n39:   sharedPayloadTransport?: string | null;\n40: };\n41: \n42: const buildStartupBrief = (_highlightCount?: number, _stateScope?: { specFolder?: string; claudeSessionId?: string }): StartupBrief =>\n43:   getStartupBriefFromMarker();\n44: \n45: /** Handle source=compact: inject cached PreCompact payload (from 3-source merger) */\n46: function handleCompact(sessionId: string): OutputSection[] {\n47:   const stateResult = loadState(sessionId);\n48:   const state = stateResult.ok ? stateResult.state : null;\n49:   const pendingCompactPrime = readCompactPrime(sessionId);\n50:   if (!pendingCompactPrime) {\n51:     hookLog('warn', 'session-prime', `No cached compact payload for session ${sessionId}`);\n52:     return [{\n53:       title: 'Context Recovery',\n54:       content: 'Context was compacted. Call `memory_context({ mode: \"resume\", profile: \"resume\" })` to recover session state.',\n55:     }];\n56:   }\n57: \n58:   const { payload, cachedAt } = pendingCompactPrime;\n59:   const cachedAtMs = new Date(cachedAt).getTime();\n60:   const cacheAgeMs = Date.now() - cachedAtMs;\n61:   if (Number.isNaN(cachedAtMs) || cacheAgeMs >= CACHE_TTL_MS) {\n62:     hookLog('warn', 'session-prime', `Rejecting stale compact cache for session ${sessionId} (cached at ${cachedAt})`);\n63:     return [{\n64:       title: 'Context Recovery',\n65:       content: 'Context was compacted. Call `memory_context({ mode: \"resume\", profile: \"resume\" })` to recover session state.',\n66:     }];\n67:   }\n68:   const semanticValidation = validatePendingCompactPrimeSemantics(pendingCompactPrime);\n69:   if (!semanticValidation.ok) {\n70:     hookLog('warn', 'session-prime', `Rejecting compact cache for session ${sessionId}: ${semanticValidation.reason}`);\n71:     clearCompactPrime(sessionId, {\n72:       cachedAt: pendingCompactPrime.cachedAt,\n73:       opaqueId: pendingCompactPrime.opaqueId ?? null,\n74:     });\n75:     return [{\n76:       title: 'Context Recovery',\n77:       content: 'Context was compacted, but the cached compact brief was quarantined by semantic validation. Call `memory_context({ mode: \"resume\", profile: \"resume\" })` to recover session state.',\n78:     }];\n79:   }\n80: \n81:   const sanitizedPayload = sanitizeRecoveredPayload(payload);\n82:   const wrappedPayload = wrapRecoveredCompactPayload(payload, cachedAt, {\n83:     producer: pendingCompactPrime.payloadContract?.provenance.producer,\n84:     trustState: pendingCompactPrime.payloadContract?.provenance.trustState,\n85:     sourceSurface: pendingCompactPrime.payloadContract?.provenance.sourceSurface,\n86:     sanitizerVersion: pendingCompactPrime.payloadContract?.provenance.sanitizerVersion,\n87:     runtimeFingerprint: pendingCompactPrime.payloadContract?.provenance.runtimeFingerprint,\n88:   });\n89:   hookLog('info', 'session-prime', `Injecting cached compact brief (${sanitizedPayload.length} chars after sanitization, cached at ${cachedAt})`);\n90: \n91:   const sections: OutputSection[] = [\n92:     { title: 'Recovered Context (Post-Compaction)', content: wrappedPayload },\n93:     {\n94:       title: 'Recovery Instructions',\n95:       content: 'Context was compacted and auto-recovered from the cached compact brief. For full session state, call `memory_context({ mode: \"resume\", profile: \"resume\" })`.',\n96:     },\n97:   ];\n98: \n99:   // Add last spec folder if known\n100:   if (state?.lastSpecFolder) {\n101:     sections.push({\n102:       title: 'Active Spec Folder',\n103:       content: `Last active: ${state.lastSpecFolder}`,\n104:     });\n105:   }\n106: \n107:   return sections;\n108: }\n109: \n110: function readCompactPrimeIdentity(sessionId: string): { cachedAt: string; opaqueId?: string | null } | null {\n111:   const pendingCompactPrime = readCompactPrime(sessionId);\n112:   if (!pendingCompactPrime) {\n113:     return null;\n114:   }\n115:   return {\n116:     cachedAt: pendingCompactPrime.cachedAt,\n117:     opaqueId: pendingCompactPrime.opaqueId ?? null,\n118:   };\n119: }\n120: \n121: /**\n122:  * Map rejection reasons to distinct short-form status labels so startup surface\n123:  * no longer collapses schema-mismatch, transcript-identity-mismatch,\n124:  * stale-summary, and ordinary missing-state into the same \"startup summary\n125:  * only\" string. Depends on HookState schema-version plumbing, which guarantees\n126:  * the upstream rejection reason is actually populated with the right\n127:  * discriminator.\n128:  */\n129: function describeMemoryStatus(\n130:   hasCachedContinuity: boolean,\n131:   rejectionReason: string | null,\n132: ): string {\n133:   if (hasCachedContinuity) {\n134:     return 'session continuity available';\n135:   }\n136:   if (!rejectionReason) {\n137:     return 'startup summary only (resume on demand)';\n138:   }\n139:   const reasonMap: Record<string, string> = {\n140:     missing_state: 'startup summary only (no cached continuity; resume on demand)',\n141:     schema_mismatch: 'startup summary only (cached continuity rejected: schema version mismatch)',\n142:     missing_summary: 'startup summary only (cached continuity rejected: missing session summary)',\n143:     missing_producer_metadata: 'startup summary only (cached continuity rejected: producer metadata missing)',\n144:     missing_required_fields: 'startup summary only (cached continuity rejected: required fields missing)',\n145:     transcript_unreadable: 'startup summary only (cached continuity rejected: transcript unreadable)',\n146:     transcript_identity_mismatch: 'startup summary only (cached continuity rejected: transcript identity mismatch)',\n147:     stale_summary: 'startup summary only (cached continuity rejected: stale summary)',\n148:     summary_precedes_producer_turn: 'startup summary only (cached continuity rejected: summary predates latest producer turn)',\n149:     scope_mismatch: 'startup summary only (cached continuity rejected: scope mismatch)',\n150:     unknown_scope: 'startup summary only (cached continuity rejected: scope unknown)',\n151:   };\n152:   return reasonMap[rejectionReason] ?? `startup summary only (cached continuity rejected: ${rejectionReason})`;\n153: }\n154: \n155: function buildFallbackStartupSurface(\n156:   hasCachedContinuity: boolean,\n157:   rejectionReason: string | null = null,\n158: ): string {\n159:   return [\n160:     'Session context received. Current state:',\n161:     '',\n162:     `- Memory: ${describeMemoryStatus(hasCachedContinuity, rejectionReason)}`,\n163:     '- Code Graph: unavailable',\n164:     '',\n165:     'What would you like to work on?',\n166:   ].join('\\n');\n167: }\n168: \n169: function rewriteStartupMemoryLine(\n170:   startupSurface: string,\n171:   hasCachedContinuity: boolean,\n172:   rejectionReason: string | null = null,\n173: ): string {\n174:   return startupSurface.replace(\n175:     /^- Memory: .*$/m,\n176:     `- Memory: ${describeMemoryStatus(hasCachedContinuity, rejectionReason)}`,\n177:   );\n178: }\n179: \n180: /** Handle source=startup: prime new session with constitutional memories + overview */\n181: export function handleStartup(\n182:   input: Pick<HookInput, 'session_id'> & { specFolder?: string } = {},\n183: ): OutputSection[] {\n184:   const sessionId = typeof input.session_id === 'string' ? input.session_id : undefined;\n185:   const requestedSpecFolder = typeof input.specFolder === 'string' ? input.specFolder : undefined;\n186:   let startupBrief: StartupBrief | null = null;\n187:   let startupBriefWarning: string | null = null;\n188:   try {\n189:     startupBrief = buildStartupBrief(undefined, {\n190:       claudeSessionId: sessionId,\n191:       specFolder: requestedSpecFolder,\n192:     });\n193:   } catch (err: unknown) {\n194:     startupBriefWarning = `buildStartupBrief threw: ${err instanceof Error ? err.message : String(err)}`;\n195:     hookLog('error', 'session-prime', startupBriefWarning);\n196:   }\n197:   if (!startupBrief) {\n198:     startupBriefWarning = 'buildStartupBrief returned null';\n199:     hookLog('warn', 'session-prime', `${startupBriefWarning} — possible startup-brief regression`);\n200:   } else if (!startupBrief.startupSurface) {\n201:     startupBriefWarning = 'startupBrief.startupSurface is empty';\n202:     hookLog('warn', 'session-prime', `${startupBriefWarning} — possible startup-brief regression`);\n203:   }\n204:   const cachedSummaryDecision = getCachedSessionSummaryDecision({\n205:     specFolder: requestedSpecFolder,\n206:     claudeSessionId: sessionId,\n207:   });\n208:   if (cachedSummaryDecision.status !== 'accepted') {\n209:     logCachedSummaryDecision('session-prime', cachedSummaryDecision);\n210:   }\n211: \n212:   const sessionContinuity = cachedSummaryDecision.status === 'accepted'\n213:     ? cachedSummaryDecision.cachedSummary?.startupHint ?? null\n214:     : null;\n215:   // Forward the rejection reason so the startup surface can\n216:   // differentiate schema_mismatch / transcript_identity_mismatch / stale_summary\n217:   // / missing_state instead of collapsing them all into \"startup summary only\".\n218:   const rejectionReason = cachedSummaryDecision.status === 'rejected'\n219:     ? cachedSummaryDecision.reason\n220:     : null;\n221:   const startupSurface = startupBrief?.startupSurface\n222:     ? rewriteStartupMemoryLine(startupBrief.startupSurface, Boolean(sessionContinuity), rejectionReason)\n223:     : buildFallbackStartupSurface(Boolean(sessionContinuity), rejectionReason);\n224:   const sections: OutputSection[] = [\n225:     {\n226:       title: 'Session Context',\n227:       content: startupSurface,\n228:     },\n229:     {\n230:       title: 'Recovery Tools',\n231:       content: [\n232:         '- `memory_context({ input, mode })` — unified context retrieval',\n233:         '- `memory_match_triggers({ prompt })` — fast trigger matching',\n234:         '- `memory_search({ query })` — semantic search',\n235:         '- `code_graph_scan`, `code_graph_query`, `code_graph_context`, `code_graph_status`',\n236:       ].join('\\n'),\n237:     },\n238:   ];\n239:   if (startupBriefWarning) {\n240:     sections.push({\n241:       title: 'Startup Brief Warning',\n242:       content: `${startupBriefWarning}. Using fallback startup context; inspect the startup-brief module before trusting structural priming.`,\n243:     });\n244:   }\n245:   if (startupBrief?.graphOutline) {\n246:     sections.push({\n247:       title: 'Structural Context',\n248:       content: startupBrief.graphOutline,\n249:     });\n250:   } else if (startupBrief?.graphState === 'empty') {\n251:     sections.push({\n252:       title: 'Structural Context',\n253:       content: 'Code graph index is empty. Run `code_graph_scan` to build structural context.',\n254:     });\n255:   }\n256: \n257:   if (startupBrief?.sharedPayloadTransport) {\n258:     sections.push({\n259:       title: 'Startup Payload Contract',\n260:       content: startupBrief.sharedPayloadTransport,\n\n(Showing lines 1-260 of 394. Use offset=261 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"#!/usr/bin/env node\n// ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// MODULE: SessionStart Hook — Session Prime\n// ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// Runs on Claude Code SessionStart event. Injects context via stdout\n// based on the session source (compact, startup, resume, clear).\n\nimport { resolve } from 'node:path';\nimport { fileURLToPath } from 'node:url';\nimport {\n  parseHookStdin, hookLog, formatHookOutput, truncateToTokenBudget,\n  withTimeout, HOOK_TIMEOUT_MS, COMPACTION_TOKEN_BUDGET, SESSION_PRIME_TOKEN_BUDGET,\n  calculatePressureAdjustedBudget, sanitizeRecoveredPayload, wrapRecoveredCompactPayload,\n  getRequiredSessionId,\n  type HookInput,\n  type OutputSection,\n} from './shared.js';\nimport {\n  ensureStateDir,\n  loadState,","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/hooks/claude/session-prime.ts","text":"#!/usr/bin/env node\n// ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// MODULE: SessionStart Hook — Session Prime\n// ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// Runs on Claude Code SessionStart event. Injects context via stdout\n// based on the session source (compact, startup, resume, clear).\n\nimport { resolve } from 'node:path';\nimport { fileURLToPath } from 'node:url';\nimport {\n  parseHookStdin, hookLog, formatHookOutput, truncateToTokenBudget,\n  withTimeout, HOOK_TIMEOUT_MS, COMPACTION_TOKEN_BUDGET, SESSION_PRIME_TOKEN_BUDGET,\n  calculatePressureAdjustedBudget, sanitizeRecoveredPayload, wrapRecoveredCompactPayload,\n  getRequiredSessionId,\n  type HookInput,\n  type OutputSection,\n} from './shared.js';\nimport {\n  ensureStateDir,\n  loadState,\n  readCompactPrime,\n  clearCompactPrime,\n  validatePendingCompactPrimeSemantics,\n} from './hook-state.js';\nimport { getCachedSessionSummaryDecision, logCachedSummaryDecision } from '../../handlers/session-resume.js';\nimport { getStartupBriefFromMarker } from '../../lib/code-graph-boundary.js';\n\nconst CACHE_TTL_MS = 30 * 60 * 1000;\nconst IS_CLI_ENTRY = process.argv[1]\n  ? resolve(process.argv[1]) === fileURLToPath(import.meta.url)\n  : false;\ntype StartupBrief = {\n  graphOutline: string | null;\n  sessionContinuity: string | null;\n  graphSummary: { files: number; nodes: number; edges: number; lastScan: string | null } | null;\n  graphQualitySummary?: unknown;\n  graphState: 'ready' | 'stale' | 'empty' | 'missing';\n  startupSurface: string;\n  sharedPayloadTransport?: string | null;\n};\n\nconst buildStartupBrief = (_highlightCount?: number, _stateScope?: { specFolder?: string; claudeSessionId?: string }): StartupBrief =>\n  getStartupBriefFromMarker();\n\n/** Handle source=compact: inject cached PreCompact payload (from 3-source merger) */\nfunction handleCompact(sessionId: string): OutputSection[] {\n  const stateResult = loadState(sessionId);\n  const state = stateResult.ok ? stateResult.state : null;\n  const pendingCompactPrime = readCompactPrime(sessionId);\n  if (!pendingCompactPrime) {\n    hookLog('warn', 'session-prime', `No cached compact payload for session ${sessionId}`);\n    return [{\n      title: 'Context Recovery',\n      content: 'Context was compacted. Call `memory_context({ mode: \"resume\", profile: \"resume\" })` to recover session state.',\n    }];\n  }\n\n  const { payload, cachedAt } = pendingCompactPrime;\n  const cachedAtMs = new Date(cachedAt).getTime();\n  const cacheAgeMs = Date.now() - cachedAtMs;\n  if (Number.isNaN(cachedAtMs) || cacheAgeMs >= CACHE_TTL_MS) {\n    hookLog('warn', 'session-prime', `Rejecting stale compact cache for session ${sessionId} (cached at ${cachedAt})`);\n    return [{\n      title: 'Context Recovery',\n      content: 'Context was compacted. Call `memory_context({ mode: \"resume\", profile: \"resume\" })` to recover session state.',\n    }];\n  }\n  const semanticValidation = validatePendingCompactPrimeSemantics(pendingCompactPrime);\n  if (!semanticValidation.ok) {\n    hookLog('warn', 'session-prime', `Rejecting compact cache for session ${sessionId}: ${semanticValidation.reason}`);\n    clearCompactPrime(sessionId, {\n      cachedAt: pendingCompactPrime.cachedAt,\n      opaqueId: pendingCompactPrime.opaqueId ?? null,\n    });\n    return [{\n      title: 'Context Recovery',\n      content: 'Context was compacted, but the cached compact brief was quarantined by semantic validation. Call `memory_context({ mode: \"resume\", profile: \"resume\" })` to recover session state.',\n    }];\n  }\n\n  const sanitizedPayload = sanitizeRecoveredPayload(payload);\n  const wrappedPayload = wrapRecoveredCompactPayload(payload, cachedAt, {\n    producer: pendingCompactPrime.payloadContract?.provenance.producer,\n    trustState: pendingCompactPrime.payloadContract?.provenance.trustState,\n    sourceSurface: pendingCompactPrime.payloadContract?.provenance.sourceSurface,\n    sanitizerVersion: pendingCompactPrime.payloadContract?.provenance.sanitizerVersion,\n    runtimeFingerprint: pendingCompactPrime.payloadContract?.provenance.runtimeFingerprint,\n  });\n  hookLog('info', 'session-prime', `Injecting cached compact brief (${sanitizedPayload.length} chars after sanitization, cached at ${cachedAt})`);\n\n  const sections: OutputSection[] = [\n    { title: 'Recovered Context (Post-Compaction)', content: wrappedPayload },\n    {\n      title: 'Recovery Instructions',\n      content: 'Context was compacted and auto-recovered from the cached compact brief. For full session state, call `memory_context({ mode: \"resume\", profile: \"resume\" })`.',\n    },\n  ];\n\n  // Add last spec folder if known\n  if (state?.lastSpecFolder) {\n    sections.push({\n      title: 'Active Spec Folder',\n      content: `Last active: ${state.lastSpecFolder}`,\n    });\n  }\n\n  return sections;\n}\n\nfunction readCompactPrimeIdentity(sessionId: string): { cachedAt: string; opaqueId?: string | null } | null {\n  const pendingCompactPrime = readCompactPrime(sessionId);\n  if (!pendingCompactPrime) {\n    return null;\n  }\n  return {\n    cachedAt: pendingCompactPrime.cachedAt,\n    opaqueId: pendingCompactPrime.opaqueId ?? null,\n  };\n}\n\n/**\n * Map rejection reasons to distinct short-form status labels so startup surface\n * no longer collapses schema-mismatch, transcript-identity-mismatch,\n * stale-summary, and ordinary missing-state into the same \"startup summary\n * only\" string. Depends on HookState schema-version plumbing, which guarantees\n * the upstream rejection reason is actually populated with the right\n * discriminator.\n */\nfunction describeMemoryStatus(\n  hasCachedContinuity: boolean,\n  rejectionReason: string | null,\n): string {\n  if (hasCachedContinuity) {\n    return 'session continuity available';\n  }\n  if (!rejectionReason) {\n    return 'startup summary only (resume on demand)';\n  }\n  const reasonMap: Record<string, string> = {\n    missing_state: 'startup summary only (no cached continuity; resume on demand)',\n    schema_mismatch: 'startup summary only (cached continuity rejected: schema version mismatch)',\n    missing_summary: 'startup summary only (cached continuity rejected: missing session summary)',\n    missing_producer_metadata: 'startup summary only (cached continuity rejected: producer metadata missing)',\n    missing_required_fields: 'startup summary only (cached continuity rejected: required fields missing)',\n    transcript_unreadable: 'startup summary only (cached continuity rejected: transcript unreadable)',\n    transcript_identity_mismatch: 'startup summary only (cached continuity rejected: transcript identity mismatch)',\n    stale_summary: 'startup summary only (cached continuity rejected: stale summary)',\n    summary_precedes_producer_turn: 'startup summary only (cached continuity rejected: summary predates latest producer turn)',\n    scope_mismatch: 'startup summary only (cached continuity rejected: scope mismatch)',\n    unknown_scope: 'startup summary only (cached continuity rejected: scope unknown)',\n  };\n  return reasonMap[rejectionReason] ?? `startup summary only (cached continuity rejected: ${rejectionReason})`;\n}\n\nfunction buildFallbackStartupSurface(\n  hasCachedContinuity: boolean,\n  rejectionReason: string | null = null,\n): string {\n  return [\n    'Session context received. Current state:',\n    '',\n    `- Memory: ${describeMemoryStatus(hasCachedContinuity, rejectionReason)}`,\n    '- Code Graph: unavailable',\n    '',\n    'What would you like to work on?',\n  ].join('\\n');\n}\n\nfunction rewriteStartupMemoryLine(\n  startupSurface: string,\n  hasCachedContinuity: boolean,\n  rejectionReason: string | null = null,\n): string {\n  return startupSurface.replace(\n    /^- Memory: .*$/m,\n    `- Memory: ${describeMemoryStatus(hasCachedContinuity, rejectionReason)}`,\n  );\n}\n\n/** Handle source=startup: prime new session with constitutional memories + overview */\nexport function handleStartup(\n  input: Pick<HookInput, 'session_id'> & { specFolder?: string } = {},\n): OutputSection[] {\n  const sessionId = typeof input.session_id === 'string' ? input.session_id : undefined;\n  const requestedSpecFolder = typeof input.specFolder === 'string' ? input.specFolder : undefined;\n  let startupBrief: StartupBrief | null = null;\n  let startupBriefWarning: string | null = null;\n  try {\n    startupBrief = buildStartupBrief(undefined, {\n      claudeSessionId: sessionId,\n      specFolder: requestedSpecFolder,\n    });\n  } catch (err: unknown) {\n    startupBriefWarning = `buildStartupBrief threw: ${err instanceof Error ? err.message : String(err)}`;\n    hookLog('error', 'session-prime', startupBriefWarning);\n  }\n  if (!startupBrief) {\n    startupBriefWarning = 'buildStartupBrief returned null';\n    hookLog('warn', 'session-prime', `${startupBriefWarning} — possible startup-brief regression`);\n  } else if (!startupBrief.startupSurface) {\n    startupBriefWarning = 'startupBrief.startupSurface is empty';\n    hookLog('warn', 'session-prime', `${startupBriefWarning} — possible startup-brief regression`);\n  }\n  const cachedSummaryDecision = getCachedSessionSummaryDecision({\n    specFolder: requestedSpecFolder,\n    claudeSessionId: sessionId,\n  });\n  if (cachedSummaryDecision.status !== 'accepted') {\n    logCachedSummaryDecision('session-prime', cachedSummaryDecision);\n  }\n\n  const sessionContinuity = cachedSummaryDecision.status === 'accepted'\n    ? cachedSummaryDecision.cachedSummary?.startupHint ?? null\n    : null;\n  // Forward the rejection reason so the startup surface can\n  // differentiate schema_mismatch / transcript_identity_mismatch / stale_summary\n  // / missing_state instead of collapsing them all into \"startup summary only\".\n  const rejectionReason = cachedSummaryDecision.status === 'rejected'\n    ? cachedSummaryDecision.reason\n    : null;\n  const startupSurface = startupBrief?.startupSurface\n    ? rewriteStartupMemoryLine(startupBrief.startupSurface, Boolean(sessionContinuity), rejectionReason)\n    : buildFallbackStartupSurface(Boolean(sessionContinuity), rejectionReason);\n  const sections: OutputSection[] = [\n    {\n      title: 'Session Context',\n      content: startupSurface,\n    },\n    {\n      title: 'Recovery Tools',\n      content: [\n        '- `memory_context({ input, mode })` — unified context retrieval',\n        '- `memory_match_triggers({ prompt })` — fast trigger matching',\n        '- `memory_search({ query })` — semantic search',\n        '- `code_graph_scan`, `code_graph_query`, `code_graph_context`, `code_graph_status`',\n      ].join('\\n'),\n    },\n  ];\n  if (startupBriefWarning) {\n    sections.push({\n      title: 'Startup Brief Warning',\n      content: `${startupBriefWarning}. Using fallback startup context; inspect the startup-brief module before trusting structural priming.`,\n    });\n  }\n  if (startupBrief?.graphOutline) {\n    sections.push({\n      title: 'Structural Context',\n      content: startupBrief.graphOutline,\n    });\n  } else if (startupBrief?.graphState === 'empty') {\n    sections.push({\n      title: 'Structural Context',\n      content: 'Code graph index is empty. Run `code_graph_scan` to build structural context.',\n    });\n  }\n\n  if (startupBrief?.sharedPayloadTransport) {\n    sections.push({\n      title: 'Startup Payload Contract',\n      content: startupBrief.sharedPayloadTransport,","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":260,"totalLines":394,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/hooks/claude/session-prime.ts","time":{"start":1780925357733,"end":1780925357754}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0f5bcb161580130a016a26c3ad9d208191a826f563ecd73284"}},"id":"prt_ea76c5ea1001ogaj38Q5hY0rGg","sessionID":"ses_158954ac7ffeX00Y2fH37dXkNJ","messageID":"msg_ea76c3e63001uhwXOldtDAOrVn"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780925357787,"sessionID":"ses_158954ac7ffeX00Y2fH37dXkNJ","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_tJ2fcRdoS7TpKTIXopZfg2Xt","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/hooks/claude/compact-inject.ts","offset":1,"limit":260},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/hooks/claude/compact-inject.ts</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: #!/usr/bin/env node\n2: // ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n3: // MODULE: PreCompact Hook — Compact Inject\n4: // ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n5: // Runs on Claude Code PreCompact event. Precomputes critical context\n6: // using the merge pipeline (Memory, Code Graph, session state)\n7: // and caches to hook state for later injection by SessionStart hook.\n8: // stdout is NOT injected on PreCompact — we only cache here.\n9: \n10: import { performance } from 'node:perf_hooks';\n11: import { readFileSync } from 'node:fs';\n12: import { pathToFileURL } from 'node:url';\n13: import {\n14:   parseHookStdin, hookLog, truncateToTokenBudget,\n15:   withTimeout, HOOK_TIMEOUT_MS, COMPACTION_TOKEN_BUDGET, getRequiredSessionId,\n16: } from './shared.js';\n17: import { ensureStateDir, updateState } from './hook-state.js';\n18: import { mergeCompactBrief, type MergeInput } from '@spec-kit/shared/compact-merger';\n19: import { autoSurfaceAtCompaction } from '../../hooks/memory-surface.js';\n20: import {\n21:   createSharedPayloadEnvelope,\n22:   createPreMergeSelectionMetadata,\n23:   type SharedPayloadEnvelope,\n24: } from '../../lib/context/shared-payload.js';\n25: import {\n26:   CANONICAL_FOLD_VERSION,\n27:   getUnicodeRuntimeFingerprint,\n28: } from '@spec-kit/shared/unicode-normalization';\n29: \n30: const COMPACT_FEEDBACK_GUARDS = [\n31:   /^\\s*\\[SOURCE:\\s*hook-cache/i,\n32:   /^\\s*\\[PROVENANCE:/i,\n33:   /^\\s*\\[\\/SOURCE\\]/i,\n34:   /^\\s*##\\s+Recovered Context/i,\n35:   /^\\s*##\\s+Recovery Instructions/i,\n36:   /\\bauto-recovered\\b/i,\n37: ];\n38: \n39: /** Extract the last N lines from a file */\n40: export function tailFile(filePath: string, lines: number): string[] {\n41:   try {\n42:     const content = readFileSync(filePath, 'utf-8');\n43:     const allLines = content.split('\\n');\n44:     return allLines.slice(Math.max(0, allLines.length - lines));\n45:   } catch {\n46:     return [];\n47:   }\n48: }\n49: \n50: /** Extract file paths mentioned in transcript lines */\n51: function extractFilePaths(lines: string[]): string[] {\n52:   const pathRegex = /(?:\\/[\\w.-]+){2,}(?:\\.\\w+)/g;\n53:   const paths = new Set<string>();\n54:   for (const line of lines) {\n55:     const matches = line.match(pathRegex);\n56:     if (matches) {\n57:       for (const m of matches) paths.add(m);\n58:     }\n59:   }\n60:   return [...paths].slice(0, 20);\n61: }\n62: \n63: /** Extract topics from recent transcript content */\n64: function extractTopics(lines: string[]): string[] {\n65:   const topics = new Set<string>();\n66:   for (const line of lines) {\n67:     const specMatch = line.match(/specs\\/[\\w-]+/g);\n68:     if (specMatch) specMatch.forEach(m => topics.add(m));\n69:     const toolMatch = line.match(/memory_\\w+|code_graph_\\w+|task_\\w+/g);\n70:     if (toolMatch) toolMatch.forEach(m => topics.add(m));\n71:   }\n72:   return [...topics].slice(0, 10);\n73: }\n74: \n75: function stripRecoveredCompactLines(lines: string[]): string[] {\n76:   return lines.filter((line) => !COMPACT_FEEDBACK_GUARDS.some((guard) => guard.test(line)));\n77: }\n78: \n79: /** Extract most-referenced identifiers from transcript lines (top 10 by frequency) */\n80: function extractAttentionSignals(lines: string[]): string[] {\n81:   const freq = new Map<string, number>();\n82:   // camelCase function calls: e.g. buildMergedContext(\n83:   const funcRe = /\\b([a-z][a-zA-Z0-9]{2,})\\s*\\(/g;\n84:   // PascalCase class/interface names: e.g. MergeInput, OutputSection\n85:   const classRe = /\\b([A-Z][a-zA-Z0-9]{2,})\\b/g;\n86:   // Common noise words to skip\n87:   const noise = new Set(['Error', 'String', 'Object', 'Array', 'Promise', 'Buffer', 'Date', 'Map', 'Set', 'Number', 'Boolean', 'Function', 'RegExp', 'JSON', 'Math', 'console', 'process', 'undefined', 'null']);\n88:   for (const line of lines) {\n89:     let m: RegExpExecArray | null;\n90:     funcRe.lastIndex = 0;\n91:     while ((m = funcRe.exec(line)) !== null) {\n92:       const id = m[1];\n93:       if (!noise.has(id) && id.length <= 60) {\n94:         freq.set(id, (freq.get(id) ?? 0) + 1);\n95:       }\n96:     }\n97:     classRe.lastIndex = 0;\n98:     while ((m = classRe.exec(line)) !== null) {\n99:       const id = m[1];\n100:       if (!noise.has(id) && id.length <= 60) {\n101:         freq.set(id, (freq.get(id) ?? 0) + 1);\n102:       }\n103:     }\n104:   }\n105:   return [...freq.entries()]\n106:     .filter(([, count]) => count >= 2)\n107:     .sort((a, b) => b[1] - a[1])\n108:     .slice(0, 10)\n109:     .map(([id, count]) => `- ${id} (referenced ${count}x)`);\n110: }\n111: \n112: /** Detect active spec folder paths from transcript lines */\n113: function detectSpecFolder(lines: string[]): string | null {\n114:   const specFolderRe = /\\.opencode\\/specs\\/[\\w/-]+/g;\n115:   const freq = new Map<string, number>();\n116:   for (const line of lines) {\n117:     const matches = line.match(specFolderRe);\n118:     if (matches) {\n119:       for (const m of matches) {\n120:         // Normalize to folder (strip trailing file component if present)\n121:         const folder = m.replace(/\\/[^/]+\\.\\w+$/, '');\n122:         freq.set(folder, (freq.get(folder) ?? 0) + 1);\n123:       }\n124:     }\n125:   }\n126:   if (freq.size === 0) return null;\n127:   // Return the most-referenced spec folder\n128:   return [...freq.entries()].sort((a, b) => b[1] - a[1])[0][0];\n129: }\n130: \n131: /** Build compact context from transcript analysis (legacy fallback) */\n132: export function buildCompactContext(transcriptLines: string[]): string {\n133:   const filePaths = extractFilePaths(transcriptLines);\n134:   const topics = extractTopics(transcriptLines);\n135:   const sections: string[] = [];\n136: \n137:   if (filePaths.length > 0) {\n138:     sections.push('## Active Files\\n' + filePaths.map(p => `- ${p}`).join('\\n'));\n139:   }\n140:   if (topics.length > 0) {\n141:     sections.push('## Recent Topics\\n' + topics.map(t => `- ${t}`).join('\\n'));\n142:   }\n143: \n144:   const meaningfulLines = transcriptLines\n145:     .filter(l => l.trim().length > 10 && !l.startsWith('{'))\n146:     .slice(-5);\n147:   if (meaningfulLines.length > 0) {\n148:     sections.push('## Recent Context\\n' + meaningfulLines.join('\\n'));\n149:   }\n150: \n151:   return sections.join('\\n\\n');\n152: }\n153: \n154: type AutoSurfaceAtCompactionResult = Awaited<ReturnType<typeof autoSurfaceAtCompaction>>;\n155: \n156: function renderConstitutionalMemories(\n157:   autoSurfaced: AutoSurfaceAtCompactionResult,\n158: ): string {\n159:   const constitutional = autoSurfaced?.constitutional ?? [];\n160:   if (constitutional.length === 0) {\n161:     return '';\n162:   }\n163: \n164:   const lines = constitutional.map((memory) => {\n165:     const details: string[] = [`- ${memory.title}`];\n166: \n167:     if (memory.retrieval_directive) {\n168:       details.push(`  ${memory.retrieval_directive}`);\n169:     }\n170: \n171:     const provenance = [memory.specFolder, memory.filePath].filter(Boolean).join(' | ');\n172:     if (provenance) {\n173:       details.push(`  ${provenance}`);\n174:     }\n175: \n176:     return details.join('\\n');\n177:   });\n178: \n179:   return `## Constitutional Rules\\n${lines.join('\\n')}`;\n180: }\n181: \n182: function renderTriggeredMemories(\n183:   autoSurfaced: AutoSurfaceAtCompactionResult,\n184: ): string {\n185:   const triggered = autoSurfaced?.triggered ?? [];\n186:   if (triggered.length === 0) {\n187:     return '';\n188:   }\n189: \n190:   const lines = triggered.map((memory) => {\n191:     const matchedPhrases = [...new Set(memory.matched_phrases\n192:       .map((phrase) => phrase.trim())\n193:       .filter((phrase) => phrase.length > 0))];\n194: \n195:     if (matchedPhrases.length === 0) {\n196:       return `- ${memory.title}`;\n197:     }\n198: \n199:     return `- ${memory.title} (matched: ${matchedPhrases.join(', ')})`;\n200:   });\n201: \n202:   return `## Relevant Memories\\n${lines.join('\\n')}`;\n203: }\n204: \n205: /**\n206:  * Build merged context using the 3-source merge pipeline.\n207:  * Extracts session state from transcript, then delegates budget allocation\n208:  * and section rendering to mergeCompactBrief.\n209:  */\n210: async function buildMergedContext(transcriptLines: string[]): Promise<string> {\n211:   const sanitizedLines = stripRecoveredCompactLines(transcriptLines);\n212:   const filePaths = extractFilePaths(sanitizedLines);\n213:   const topics = extractTopics(sanitizedLines);\n214: \n215:   // Build codeGraph input: active files + structural hints\n216:   const codeGraphParts: string[] = [];\n217:   if (filePaths.length > 0) {\n218:     codeGraphParts.push('Active files:\\n' + filePaths.map(p => `- ${p}`).join('\\n'));\n219:   }\n220:   const codeGraph = codeGraphParts.join('\\n\\n');\n221: \n222:   // Build sessionState input: recent context + topics + attention signals\n223:   const sessionParts: string[] = [];\n224: \n225:   // Spec folder detection\n226:   const specFolder = detectSpecFolder(sanitizedLines);\n227:   if (specFolder) {\n228:     sessionParts.push(`Active spec folder: ${specFolder}`);\n229:   }\n230: \n231:   // Working memory attention signals\n232:   const attentionSignals = extractAttentionSignals(sanitizedLines);\n233:   if (attentionSignals.length > 0) {\n234:     sessionParts.push('Working memory attention:\\n' + attentionSignals.join('\\n'));\n235:   }\n236: \n237:   if (topics.length > 0) {\n238:     sessionParts.push('Recent topics:\\n' + topics.map(t => `- ${t}`).join('\\n'));\n239:   }\n240:   const meaningfulLines = sanitizedLines\n241:     .filter(l => l.trim().length > 10 && !l.startsWith('{'))\n242:     .slice(-5);\n243:   if (meaningfulLines.length > 0) {\n244:     sessionParts.push('Recent context:\\n' + meaningfulLines.join('\\n'));\n245:   }\n246:   const sessionState = sessionParts.join('\\n\\n');\n247: \n248:   const selection = createPreMergeSelectionMetadata({\n249:     selectedFrom: ['transcript-tail', 'active-files', 'recent-topics', 'attention-signals'],\n250:     fileCount: filePaths.length,\n251:     topicCount: topics.length,\n252:     attentionSignalCount: attentionSignals.length,\n253:     notes: [\n254:       sanitizedLines.length !== transcriptLines.length\n255:         ? 'Recovered compact transcript lines were removed before pre-merge selection.'\n256:         : 'No recovered compact transcript lines detected in the current tail.',\n257:       specFolder ? `Spec folder anchored: ${specFolder}` : 'No active spec folder detected in transcript tail.',\n258:     ],\n259:     antiFeedbackGuards: [\n260:       'Strip recovered hook-cache source markers before transcript summarization.',\n\n(Showing lines 1-260 of 461. Use offset=261 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"#!/usr/bin/env node\n// ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// MODULE: PreCompact Hook — Compact Inject\n// ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// Runs on Claude Code PreCompact event. Precomputes critical context\n// using the merge pipeline (Memory, Code Graph, session state)\n// and caches to hook state for later injection by SessionStart hook.\n// stdout is NOT injected on PreCompact — we only cache here.\n\nimport { performance } from 'node:perf_hooks';\nimport { readFileSync } from 'node:fs';\nimport { pathToFileURL } from 'node:url';\nimport {\n  parseHookStdin, hookLog, truncateToTokenBudget,\n  withTimeout, HOOK_TIMEOUT_MS, COMPACTION_TOKEN_BUDGET, getRequiredSessionId,\n} from './shared.js';\nimport { ensureStateDir, updateState } from './hook-state.js';\nimport { mergeCompactBrief, type MergeInput } from '@spec-kit/shared/compact-merger';\nimport { autoSurfaceAtCompaction } from '../../hooks/memory-surface.js';\nimport {","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/hooks/claude/compact-inject.ts","text":"#!/usr/bin/env node\n// ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// MODULE: PreCompact Hook — Compact Inject\n// ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// Runs on Claude Code PreCompact event. Precomputes critical context\n// using the merge pipeline (Memory, Code Graph, session state)\n// and caches to hook state for later injection by SessionStart hook.\n// stdout is NOT injected on PreCompact — we only cache here.\n\nimport { performance } from 'node:perf_hooks';\nimport { readFileSync } from 'node:fs';\nimport { pathToFileURL } from 'node:url';\nimport {\n  parseHookStdin, hookLog, truncateToTokenBudget,\n  withTimeout, HOOK_TIMEOUT_MS, COMPACTION_TOKEN_BUDGET, getRequiredSessionId,\n} from './shared.js';\nimport { ensureStateDir, updateState } from './hook-state.js';\nimport { mergeCompactBrief, type MergeInput } from '@spec-kit/shared/compact-merger';\nimport { autoSurfaceAtCompaction } from '../../hooks/memory-surface.js';\nimport {\n  createSharedPayloadEnvelope,\n  createPreMergeSelectionMetadata,\n  type SharedPayloadEnvelope,\n} from '../../lib/context/shared-payload.js';\nimport {\n  CANONICAL_FOLD_VERSION,\n  getUnicodeRuntimeFingerprint,\n} from '@spec-kit/shared/unicode-normalization';\n\nconst COMPACT_FEEDBACK_GUARDS = [\n  /^\\s*\\[SOURCE:\\s*hook-cache/i,\n  /^\\s*\\[PROVENANCE:/i,\n  /^\\s*\\[\\/SOURCE\\]/i,\n  /^\\s*##\\s+Recovered Context/i,\n  /^\\s*##\\s+Recovery Instructions/i,\n  /\\bauto-recovered\\b/i,\n];\n\n/** Extract the last N lines from a file */\nexport function tailFile(filePath: string, lines: number): string[] {\n  try {\n    const content = readFileSync(filePath, 'utf-8');\n    const allLines = content.split('\\n');\n    return allLines.slice(Math.max(0, allLines.length - lines));\n  } catch {\n    return [];\n  }\n}\n\n/** Extract file paths mentioned in transcript lines */\nfunction extractFilePaths(lines: string[]): string[] {\n  const pathRegex = /(?:\\/[\\w.-]+){2,}(?:\\.\\w+)/g;\n  const paths = new Set<string>();\n  for (const line of lines) {\n    const matches = line.match(pathRegex);\n    if (matches) {\n      for (const m of matches) paths.add(m);\n    }\n  }\n  return [...paths].slice(0, 20);\n}\n\n/** Extract topics from recent transcript content */\nfunction extractTopics(lines: string[]): string[] {\n  const topics = new Set<string>();\n  for (const line of lines) {\n    const specMatch = line.match(/specs\\/[\\w-]+/g);\n    if (specMatch) specMatch.forEach(m => topics.add(m));\n    const toolMatch = line.match(/memory_\\w+|code_graph_\\w+|task_\\w+/g);\n    if (toolMatch) toolMatch.forEach(m => topics.add(m));\n  }\n  return [...topics].slice(0, 10);\n}\n\nfunction stripRecoveredCompactLines(lines: string[]): string[] {\n  return lines.filter((line) => !COMPACT_FEEDBACK_GUARDS.some((guard) => guard.test(line)));\n}\n\n/** Extract most-referenced identifiers from transcript lines (top 10 by frequency) */\nfunction extractAttentionSignals(lines: string[]): string[] {\n  const freq = new Map<string, number>();\n  // camelCase function calls: e.g. buildMergedContext(\n  const funcRe = /\\b([a-z][a-zA-Z0-9]{2,})\\s*\\(/g;\n  // PascalCase class/interface names: e.g. MergeInput, OutputSection\n  const classRe = /\\b([A-Z][a-zA-Z0-9]{2,})\\b/g;\n  // Common noise words to skip\n  const noise = new Set(['Error', 'String', 'Object', 'Array', 'Promise', 'Buffer', 'Date', 'Map', 'Set', 'Number', 'Boolean', 'Function', 'RegExp', 'JSON', 'Math', 'console', 'process', 'undefined', 'null']);\n  for (const line of lines) {\n    let m: RegExpExecArray | null;\n    funcRe.lastIndex = 0;\n    while ((m = funcRe.exec(line)) !== null) {\n      const id = m[1];\n      if (!noise.has(id) && id.length <= 60) {\n        freq.set(id, (freq.get(id) ?? 0) + 1);\n      }\n    }\n    classRe.lastIndex = 0;\n    while ((m = classRe.exec(line)) !== null) {\n      const id = m[1];\n      if (!noise.has(id) && id.length <= 60) {\n        freq.set(id, (freq.get(id) ?? 0) + 1);\n      }\n    }\n  }\n  return [...freq.entries()]\n    .filter(([, count]) => count >= 2)\n    .sort((a, b) => b[1] - a[1])\n    .slice(0, 10)\n    .map(([id, count]) => `- ${id} (referenced ${count}x)`);\n}\n\n/** Detect active spec folder paths from transcript lines */\nfunction detectSpecFolder(lines: string[]): string | null {\n  const specFolderRe = /\\.opencode\\/specs\\/[\\w/-]+/g;\n  const freq = new Map<string, number>();\n  for (const line of lines) {\n    const matches = line.match(specFolderRe);\n    if (matches) {\n      for (const m of matches) {\n        // Normalize to folder (strip trailing file component if present)\n        const folder = m.replace(/\\/[^/]+\\.\\w+$/, '');\n        freq.set(folder, (freq.get(folder) ?? 0) + 1);\n      }\n    }\n  }\n  if (freq.size === 0) return null;\n  // Return the most-referenced spec folder\n  return [...freq.entries()].sort((a, b) => b[1] - a[1])[0][0];\n}\n\n/** Build compact context from transcript analysis (legacy fallback) */\nexport function buildCompactContext(transcriptLines: string[]): string {\n  const filePaths = extractFilePaths(transcriptLines);\n  const topics = extractTopics(transcriptLines);\n  const sections: string[] = [];\n\n  if (filePaths.length > 0) {\n    sections.push('## Active Files\\n' + filePaths.map(p => `- ${p}`).join('\\n'));\n  }\n  if (topics.length > 0) {\n    sections.push('## Recent Topics\\n' + topics.map(t => `- ${t}`).join('\\n'));\n  }\n\n  const meaningfulLines = transcriptLines\n    .filter(l => l.trim().length > 10 && !l.startsWith('{'))\n    .slice(-5);\n  if (meaningfulLines.length > 0) {\n    sections.push('## Recent Context\\n' + meaningfulLines.join('\\n'));\n  }\n\n  return sections.join('\\n\\n');\n}\n\ntype AutoSurfaceAtCompactionResult = Awaited<ReturnType<typeof autoSurfaceAtCompaction>>;\n\nfunction renderConstitutionalMemories(\n  autoSurfaced: AutoSurfaceAtCompactionResult,\n): string {\n  const constitutional = autoSurfaced?.constitutional ?? [];\n  if (constitutional.length === 0) {\n    return '';\n  }\n\n  const lines = constitutional.map((memory) => {\n    const details: string[] = [`- ${memory.title}`];\n\n    if (memory.retrieval_directive) {\n      details.push(`  ${memory.retrieval_directive}`);\n    }\n\n    const provenance = [memory.specFolder, memory.filePath].filter(Boolean).join(' | ');\n    if (provenance) {\n      details.push(`  ${provenance}`);\n    }\n\n    return details.join('\\n');\n  });\n\n  return `## Constitutional Rules\\n${lines.join('\\n')}`;\n}\n\nfunction renderTriggeredMemories(\n  autoSurfaced: AutoSurfaceAtCompactionResult,\n): string {\n  const triggered = autoSurfaced?.triggered ?? [];\n  if (triggered.length === 0) {\n    return '';\n  }\n\n  const lines = triggered.map((memory) => {\n    const matchedPhrases = [...new Set(memory.matched_phrases\n      .map((phrase) => phrase.trim())\n      .filter((phrase) => phrase.length > 0))];\n\n    if (matchedPhrases.length === 0) {\n      return `- ${memory.title}`;\n    }\n\n    return `- ${memory.title} (matched: ${matchedPhrases.join(', ')})`;\n  });\n\n  return `## Relevant Memories\\n${lines.join('\\n')}`;\n}\n\n/**\n * Build merged context using the 3-source merge pipeline.\n * Extracts session state from transcript, then delegates budget allocation\n * and section rendering to mergeCompactBrief.\n */\nasync function buildMergedContext(transcriptLines: string[]): Promise<string> {\n  const sanitizedLines = stripRecoveredCompactLines(transcriptLines);\n  const filePaths = extractFilePaths(sanitizedLines);\n  const topics = extractTopics(sanitizedLines);\n\n  // Build codeGraph input: active files + structural hints\n  const codeGraphParts: string[] = [];\n  if (filePaths.length > 0) {\n    codeGraphParts.push('Active files:\\n' + filePaths.map(p => `- ${p}`).join('\\n'));\n  }\n  const codeGraph = codeGraphParts.join('\\n\\n');\n\n  // Build sessionState input: recent context + topics + attention signals\n  const sessionParts: string[] = [];\n\n  // Spec folder detection\n  const specFolder = detectSpecFolder(sanitizedLines);\n  if (specFolder) {\n    sessionParts.push(`Active spec folder: ${specFolder}`);\n  }\n\n  // Working memory attention signals\n  const attentionSignals = extractAttentionSignals(sanitizedLines);\n  if (attentionSignals.length > 0) {\n    sessionParts.push('Working memory attention:\\n' + attentionSignals.join('\\n'));\n  }\n\n  if (topics.length > 0) {\n    sessionParts.push('Recent topics:\\n' + topics.map(t => `- ${t}`).join('\\n'));\n  }\n  const meaningfulLines = sanitizedLines\n    .filter(l => l.trim().length > 10 && !l.startsWith('{'))\n    .slice(-5);\n  if (meaningfulLines.length > 0) {\n    sessionParts.push('Recent context:\\n' + meaningfulLines.join('\\n'));\n  }\n  const sessionState = sessionParts.join('\\n\\n');\n\n  const selection = createPreMergeSelectionMetadata({\n    selectedFrom: ['transcript-tail', 'active-files', 'recent-topics', 'attention-signals'],\n    fileCount: filePaths.length,\n    topicCount: topics.length,\n    attentionSignalCount: attentionSignals.length,\n    notes: [\n      sanitizedLines.length !== transcriptLines.length\n        ? 'Recovered compact transcript lines were removed before pre-merge selection.'\n        : 'No recovered compact transcript lines detected in the current tail.',\n      specFolder ? `Spec folder anchored: ${specFolder}` : 'No active spec folder detected in transcript tail.',\n    ],\n    antiFeedbackGuards: [\n      'Strip recovered hook-cache source markers before transcript summarization.',","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":260,"totalLines":461,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/hooks/claude/compact-inject.ts","time":{"start":1780925357738,"end":1780925357783}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0f5bcb161580130a016a26c3ad9d288191a5c89827ae61779f"}},"id":"prt_ea76c5ea7001GIAyRWlSVCWidF","sessionID":"ses_158954ac7ffeX00Y2fH37dXkNJ","messageID":"msg_ea76c3e63001uhwXOldtDAOrVn"}}
